term.name: cell
term.def: anatomical structure that has as its parts a maximally connected cell compartment surrounded by a plasma membrane.

term.name: cell by organism
term.def: a classification of cells by the organisms within which they are contained.

term.name: non-terminally differentiated cell
term.def: a precursor cell with a limited number of potential fates.

term.name: cell by histology
term.def: a classification of cells by their microscopical appearance.

term.name: epithelial cell
term.def: a cell that is usually found in a two-dimensional sheet with a free surface.

term.name: cell by function
term.def: a classification of cells by their primary end goal or behavior.

term.name: melanocyte
term.def: a pigment cell derived from the neural crest. contains melanin-filled pigment granules, which gives a brown to black appearance.

term.name: motile cell
term.def: a cell that moves by its own activities.

term.name: ectodermal cell
term.def: a cell of the outer of the three germ layers of the embryo.

term.name: stuff accumulating cell
term.def: a cell that is specialised to accumulate a particular substance(s).

term.name: neural crest cell
term.def: a cell of the strip of specialized ectoderm flanking each side of the embryonal neural plate, which after the closure of the neural tube, forms a column of isolated cells along the dorsal aspect of the neural tube. most of the cranial and all of the spinal sensory ganglion cells arise by differentiation of neural crest cells.

term.name: melanoblast
term.def: a cell that originates from the neural crest and differentiates into a pigment cell.

term.name: angiosarcoma
term.def: a sarcoma that results_in rapidly proliferating, extensively infiltrating anaplastic cells derived_from blood vessels and derived_from the lining of irregular blood-filled spaces.

term.name: disease of metabolism
term.def: a disease that involving errors in metabolic processes.

term.name: cutaneous strongyloidiasis
term.def: a strongyloidiasis that involves parasitic infection by the filariform larvae of strongyloides stercoralis, which penetrate the human skin causing urticarial rashes in the buttocks and waist areas.

term.name: intestinal strongyloidiasis
term.def: a strongyloidiasis that involves infection of intestine with strongyloides stercoralis, which results in abdominal pain, diarrhea, ileus, massive gastrointestinal bleeding, severe malabsorption, and peritonitis.

term.name: mansonella perstans infectious disease
term.def: a mansonelliasis that involves parasitic infection by the nematode mansonella perstans, which resides in body cavities and the surrounding tissues causing angioedema, pruritus, fever, headaches, arthralgias, and neurologic manifestations. midges transmit the disease.

term.name: mansonella streptocerca infectious disease
term.def: a mansonelliasis that involves parasitic infection by the nematode mansonella streptocerca, which resides in the dermis and subcutaneous tissue causing pruritus, papular eruptions and pigmentation changes. midges transmit the disease.

term.name: chikungunya
term.def: an alphavirus infectious disease and is_a arthritis that results_in infection located_in joint, has_agent chikungunya virus, which is transmitted_by aedes mosquito bite. the infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom arthralgia, and has_symptom maculopapular rash.

term.name: epizootic hemorrhagic disease
term.def: an orbivirus infectious disease that results_in infection in deer, has_agent epizootic hemorrhagic disease virus, which is transmitted_by culicoides biting midges. the infection has_symptom hemorrhages in many tissues including the skin, heart, and gastrointestinal tract, and has_symptom ulcers of the tongue, dental pad, palate, rumen, and omasum.

term.name: rocio virus encephalitis
term.def: a flavivirus infectious disease and is_a viral encephalitis that results_in inflammation located_in brain, has_agent rocio virus, which is transmitted_by psorophora ferox and transmitted_by aedes species of mosquitoes. the infection has_symptom abdominal distension, has_symptom confusion, has_symptom motor impairment, has_symptom difficulty in walking and maintaining balance, has_symptom meningeal irritation, and has_symptom cerebellar syndrome.

term.name: adiaspiromycosis
term.def: a primary systemic ascomycota mycosis that is a fungal infection located_in lungs, or located_in skin, which results_in disseminated granulomatous pulmonary process and cutaneous infection in rodents, small wild mammals and humans, has_agent chrysosporium parvum.

term.name: invasive pulmonary aspergillosis
term.def: an aspergillosis and is_a lung disease that is a serious fungal infection of the lung with pneumonia caused by aspergillus, which spreads to other parts of the body through bloodstream in patients with acute leukemia and recipients of tissue transplants. clinical symptoms include pulmonary nodules and hemorrhage.

term.name: tonsillar aspergillosis
term.def: an aspergillosis that involves fungal infection of the tonsils by aspergillus species.

term.name: pulmonary blastomycosis
term.def: a blastomycosis and is_a lung disease that results_in fungal infection located_in lungs, has_agent blastomyces dermatitidis, transmitted_by airborne spores and has_symptom lung lesions, has_symptom pleural thickening and results_in_formation_of pulmonary nodules.

term.name: hepatic torque teno virus infectious disease
term.def: an anelloviridae infectious disease and is_a liver disease that results_in infection located_in liver, has_agent torque teno virus, which is transmitted_by blood transfusion.

term.name: rhinotracheitis
term.def: an upper respiratory tract disease involving inflammation of the nasal cavities and trachea caused by feline herpesvirus 1, of the family herpesviridae in cats and especially young kittens that is characterized by sneezing, conjunctivitis with discharge, and nasal discharges.

term.name: entomophthoromycosis
term.def: a subcutaneous fungi incertae sedis mycosis that involves fungal infection of the subcutaneous tissue caused by members of the order entomophthorales.

term.name: cutaneous mucormycosis
term.def: a mucormycosis and is_a subcutaneous fungi incertae sedis mycosis that results_in fungal infection located_in cutaneous tissues or located_in subcutaneous tissues followed by a traumatic implantation of fungal elements through the skin, has_agent mucorales molds and has_symptom necrotic lesions which progressively evolve from the epidermis into dermis and even muscle.

term.name: gastrointestinal mucormycosis
term.def: a mucormycosis and is_a gastrointestinal system infectious disease that results_in fungal infection located_in gastrointestinal tract, has_agent mucorales molds in immunocompromised patients, results_in_formation_of intra-abdominal abscess and has_symptom abdominal pain, has_symptom distention, has_symptom nausea, and has_symptom vomiting.

term.name: pulmonary mucormycosis
term.def: a mucormycosis and is_a lung disease that results_in fungal infection located_in lungs, has_agent mucorales molds and has_symptom hemoptysis and has-symptom necrosis.

term.name: rhinocerebral mucormycosis
term.def: a mucormycosis that results_in fungal infection located_in nose, located_in sinuses, located_in eyes, and located_in brain of immunocompromised individuals and has_symptom orbital cellulitis, has_symptom proptosis, has_symptom pus discharge from the nose, and has_symptom seizures.

term.name: disseminated paracoccidioidomycosis
term.def: a paracoccidioidomycosis that results_in systemic fungal infection through hematogenous spread, has_agent paracoccidioides brasiliensis.

term.name: pulmonary paracoccidioidomycosis
term.def: a paracoccidioidomycosis and is_a lung disease that results_in inflammation located_in lungs, has_agent paracoccidioides brasiliensis and has_symptom cough, has_symptom fever, has_symptom night sweats, has_symptom malaise, and has_symptom weight loss.

term.name: disseminated sporotrichosis
term.def: a sporotrichosis that results_in systemic fungal infection through hematogenous spread, has_agent sporothrix schenckii, a dimorphic fungus.

term.name: lymphocutaneous sporotrichosis
term.def: a sporotrichosis that results_in fungal infection located_in skin and located_in subcutaneous tissue, and located_in lymphatic vessel through direct inoculation from wood splinters or hay, has_agent sporothrix schenckii, a dimorphic fungus, which results_in_formation_of erythematous papulonodular lesions at the site of implantation and along the lymphangitic channels which soon become palpable and ulcerate.

term.name: pulmonary sporotrichosis
term.def: a sporotrichosis and is_a lung disease that results_in fungal infection located_in lung, has_agent sporothrix schenckii, a dimorphic fungus, which is transmitted_by airborne spores and has_symptom productive cough, has_symptom nodules and cavitations of the lungs, has_symptom fibrosis, and has_symptom swollen hilar lymph nodes.

term.name: tinea barbae
term.def: a dermatophytosis that results_in fungal infection which effects horny layer of epidermis of the bearded areas located_in face and located_in neck, has_agent trichophyton mentagrophytes or has_agent trichophyton verrucosum, which also effects hair, and effects nail and has_symptom inflammatory kerion-like plaques, and results_in_formation_of noninflammatory superficial perifollicular pustules.

term.name: ectothrix infectious disease
term.def: a tinea capitis that results_in fungal infection located_in cuticle of hair, has_agent microsporum canis, has_agent microsporum gypseum, has_agent trichophyton equinum, and has_agent trichophyton verrucosum, which produce arthroconidia on the exterior of the hair shaft.

term.name: microsporum audouinii tinea capitis
term.def: an ectothrix infectious disease that results_in non-inflammatory fungal infection located_in scalp and located_in skin, has_agent microsporum audouinii.

term.name: microsporum canis tinea capitis
term.def: an ectothrix infectious disease that results_in zoophilic fungal infection located_in hair, located_in skin, and located_in nail, has_agent microsporum canis.

term.name: microsporum distortum tinea capitis
term.def: an ectothrix infectious disease that results_in zoophilic fungal infection located_in skin, and located_in hair, has_agent microsporum distortum, which causes infections in cats, dogs and other animals.

term.name: microsporum ferrugineum tinea capitis
term.def: an ectothrix infectious disease that results_in anthropophilic fungal infection located_in skin and located_in hair, has_agent microsporum ferrugineum.

term.name: microsporum gypseum tinea capitis
term.def: an ectothrix infectious disease that results_in geophilic fungal infection located_in glabrous skin, located_in scalp and located_in hair, has_agent microsporum gypseum, which results_in_formation_of inflammatory lesions.

term.name: microsporum nanum tinea capitis
term.def: an ectothrix infectious disease that results_in geophilic and zoophilic fungal infection located_in skin, located_in scalp and located_in hair, has_agent microsporum nanum, which results_in_formation_of chronic non-inflammatory lesions in pigs and humans.

term.name: trichophyton verrucosum tinea capitis
term.def: an ectothrix infectious disease that results_in zoophilic inflammatory fungal infection located_in skin, located_in beard, located_in scalp and located_in nail in cattle and humans, has-agent trichophyton verrucosum.

term.name: endothrix infectious disease
term.def: a tinea capitis that results_in fungal infection located_in hair, has_agent ascomycota fungi that belong to a group called dermatophytes, which produce arthroconidia within the hair shaft only.

term.name: trichophyton soudanense tinea capitis
term.def: an endothrix infectious disease that results_in anthropophilic fungal infection located_in scalp and located_in hair, has_agent trichophyton soudanense.

term.name: trichophyton tonsurans tinea capitis
term.def: an endothrix infectious disease that results_in anthropophilic fungal infection located_in skin, located_in nail and located_in scalp, has_agent trichophyton tonsurans and results_in_formation_of scaling lesions.

term.name: trichophyton violaceum tinea capitis
term.def: an endothrix infectious disease that results_in anthropophilic fungal infection located_in skin, located_in nail, located_in beard, and located_in scalp, has_agent trichophyton violaceum and results_in_formation_of scaling lesions. the hairs become notably fragile and break easily at the level of the scalp. the rest of the infected follicle looks like \black dots\.

term.name: trichophyton schoenleinii tinea capitis
term.def: a tinea favosa that results_in anthropophilic fungal infection located_in scalp, has_agent trichophyton schoenleinii. it is a chronic, scarring form of tinea capitis, which results_in_formation_of scutula and has_symptom permanent hair loss.

term.name: microsporum fulvum tinea capitis
term.def: an ectothrix infectious disease that results_in geophilic fungal infection located_in scalp and located_in hair in humans and animals, has_agent microsporum fulvum.

term.name: trichophyton megninii tinea capitis
term.def: an ectothrix infectious disease that results_in anthropophilic fungal infection located_in scalp and located_in hair, has_agent trichophyton megninii.

term.name: trichophyton equinum tinea capitis
term.def: an ectothrix infectious disease that results_in zoophilic fungal infection located_in scalp and located_in hair, has_agent trichophyton equinum.

term.name: trichophyton yaoundei tinea capitis
term.def: an endothrix infectious disease that results_in anthropophilic fungal infection located_in scalp and located_in hair, has_agent trichophyton yaoundei, results_in_formation_of lesions.

term.name: tinea imbricata
term.def: a tinea corporis that results_in fungal infection located_in skin, has_agent trichophyton concentricum, which is characterized by ring-like growth in overlapping circles that may have an autosomal dominant genetic predisposition.

term.name: disease by infectious agent
term.def: a disease that is the consequence of the presence of pathogenic microbial agents, including pathogenic viruses, pathogenic bacteria, fungi, protozoa, multicellular parasites, and aberrant proteins known as prions.

term.name: la crosse encephalitis
term.def: a california virus encephalitis that results_in inflammation located_in brain, has_agent la crosse virus, which is transmitted_by treehole mosquito, ochlerotatus triseriatus. the infection has_symptom seizures, has_symptom headache, has_symptom fever, has_symptom coma, and has_symptom paralysis.

term.name: west nile virus neurological syndrome
term.def: a west nile virus infectious disease that has_agent west nile virus, which can cause meningitis, encephalitis, acute laccid paralysis, parkingsonian-like conditions or movement disorder.

term.name: hemophagocytic lymphohistiocytosis
term.def: a lymphatic system disease that is characterized by an expansion of the monocyte-macrophage population and intense hemophagocytosis. it can occur de novo, but more often occurs in the setting of another disorder, usually an infection or a malignancy. a clinical picture of fever, hepatosplenomegaly, lymphadenopathy and peripheral pancytopenia. the morphologic hallmark of this syndrome is the phagocytosis of hematopoietic elements by morphologically normal macrophages.

term.name: dengue shock syndrome
term.def: a dengue disease that involves the most severe form of dengue fever, has_agent dengue virus

term.name: tahyna virus encephalitis
term.def: a california virus encephalitis that results_in inflammation located_in brain, has_agent tahyna virus, which is transmitted_by aedes, transmitted_by culex, and transmitted_by ochlerotatus mosquitoes. the infection has_symptom headache, has_symptom fever, has_symptom anorexia, and has_symptom seizures.

term.name: sinusitis
term.def: a paranasal sinus disease involving inflammation of the paranasal sinuses resulting from bacterial, fungal, viral infection, allergic or autoimmune issues. symptoms can include fever, weakness, fatigue, cough and congestion. there may also be mucus drainage in the back of the throat, called postnasal drip.

term.name: secretory diarrhea
term.def: secretory diarrhea is a diarrhea where there is an increase in the active secretion, or there is an inhibition of absorption causing little to no structural damage. the most common cause of this type of diarrhea is a cholera toxin that stimulates the secretion of anions, especially chloride ions.

term.name: osmotic diarrhea
term.def: osmotic diarrhea is a dirrhea where diarrhea occurs when too much water is drawn into the bowels. this can be the result of maldigestion (e.g., pancreatic disease or coeliac disease), in which the nutrients are left in the lumen to pull in water. osmotic diarrhea can also be caused by osmotic laxatives (which work to alleviate constipation by drawing water into the bowels). in healthy individuals, too much magnesium or vitamin c or undigested lactose can produce osmotic diarrhea and distention of the bowel. a person who does not have lactose intolerance can have difficulty absorbing lactose after an extraordinarily high intake of dairy products.

term.name: motility-related diarrhea
term.def: motility-related diarrhea is a diarrhea which is caused by the rapid movement of food through the intestines (hypermotility). if the food moves too quickly through the gi tract, there is not enough time for sufficient nutrients and water to be absorbed.

term.name: inflammatory diarrhea
term.def: a gastrointestinal system infectious disease involving diarrhea that occurs when there is damage to the mucosal lining or brush border, which leads to a passive loss of protein-rich fluids, and a decreased ability to absorb these lost fluids. it can be caused by bacterial infections, viral infections, parasitic infections, or autoimmune problems such as inflammatory bowel diseases. it can also be caused by tuberculosis, colon cancer, and enteritis.

term.name: superficial mycosis
term.def: a fungal infectious disease that results_in infection of the outermost layer located_in skin or located_in hair shaft, has_agent fungi. no living tissue is invaded and there is no cellular response from the host.

term.name: cutaneous mycosis
term.def: a fungal infectious disease that results_in infection of the keratinized layers located_in skin, located_in hair and located_in nail, which extends deeper into the epidermis, has_agent fungi and results_in_formation_of skin lesions.

term.name: subcutaneous mycosis
term.def: a fungal infectious disease that results_in infection located_in skin and located_in subcutaneous tissue, has_agent fungi, which penetrate the dermis or even deeper during or after a skin trauma.

term.name: systemic mycosis
term.def: a fungal infectious disease that results_in infection of internal organs and tissues located_in human body, has_agent fungi, which enter the body via the respiratory tract, through the gut, paranasal sinuses or skin and spread through the bloodstream to multiple organs.

term.name: opisthorchis felineus infectious disease
term.def: a opisthorchiasis that involves parasitic infection of the liver, biliary ducts, pancreas and pancreatic ducts by opisthorchis felineus. the symptoms include fever, general malaise, skin rash, gastrointestinal disturbances, severe anemia and liver damage.

term.name: acute diarrhea
term.def: a diarrhea that is of rapid onset and course characterized by frequent loose or liquid bowel movements. acute diarrhea is a common cause of death in developing countries and the second most common cause of infant deaths worldwide.

term.name: intestinal botulism
term.def: a botulism that involves intoxication caused by botulinum neurotoxins (bonta, b, e and f) in adults, has_agent clostridium botulinum a, has_agent clostridium botulinum b, has_agent clostridium botulinum e and has_agent clostridium botulinum f, which are transmitted_by ingestion of bacterial spores, which then grow in the intestine and release toxins.

term.name: asymptomatic dengue
term.def: a dengue disease that results_in infection, has_agent dengue virus

term.name: kartagener syndrome
term.def: a syndrome consisting of triad of sinusitis, bronchiectasis and situs inversus with dextrocardia.

term.name: adenoiditis
term.def: an upper respiratory tract disease which involves inflammation, pain, and swelling of the adenoid tissue due to the infection by bacteria and viruses. it occurs primarily in children and may be secondary to an allergy, infection of nose or throat and an obstruction of the eustachian tube. the symptoms include pain, redness, swelling, and difficulty swallowing.

term.name: otomycosis
term.def: a otitis externa which is a disease of the ear produced by the growth of fungi in the external auditory canal. it is characterized by inflammation, pruritus, scaling and severe discomfort. the most common fungi are aspergillus niger and candida albicans.

term.name: laryngotracheitis
term.def: an upper respiratory tract disease involving inflammation of both larynx and trachea often caused by viral infection. the infection can close off the windpipe.

term.name: pontiac fever
term.def: a legionellosis that involves a milder respiratory illness without pneumonia. symptoms include fever, headache and muscle aches which last for 2 to 5 days.

term.name: tracheobronchial tuberculosis
term.def: a pulmonary tuberculosis involving inflammation of trachea and bronchi. the symptoms include dry cough followed by dyspnea, localized wheezing, hemoptysis, hoarseness, anorexia, weight loss, chest pain and fever.

term.name: aspiration pneumonia
term.def: a bacterial pneumonia which is an acute pulmonary inflammatory response that develops after the inhalation of colonized oropharyngeal material containing bacteria. it is seen in individuals with dysphagia and gastric dysmotility. the symptoms include tachypnea and cough.

term.name: pulmonary aspergilloma
term.def: an aspergillosis and is_a lung disease that presents as a clump of tangled mass of aspergillus fungus fibres, blood clots, and white blood cells, which exists in the cavities of the lungs that develop in an area of previous lung disease or lung scarring.

term.name: mycoplasmal pneumonia
term.def: a primary mycoplasma infectious disease and is_a bacterial pneumonia caused by the genus mycoplasma.

term.name: sensory system disease
term.def: a body system disease which is located in a part of the nervous system responsible for processing sensory information that consists of sensory receptors, neural pathways, and parts of the brain involved in sensory perception. commonly recognized sensory systems are those for vision, hearing, somatic sensation (touch), taste and olfaction (smell).

term.name: idiopathic pulmonary fibrosis
term.def: a idiopathic interstitial pneumonia which is a distinctive type of chronic fibrosing interstitial pneumonia with thick scarring in the lung creating a honeycomb appearance. the main symptoms start insidiously as shortness of breath on exertion, cough, and diminished stamina. other common complaints include weight loss and fatigue. the level of oxygen in the blood decreases, and the skin may take on a bluish tinge (called cyanosis) and the ends of the fingers may become thick or club-shape. in most people, symptoms worsen over a period ranging from about 6 months to several years.

term.name: cryptogenic organizing pneumonia
term.def: a idiopathic interstitial pneumonia characterized by lung inflammation and scarring that obstructs the small airways and air sacs of the lungs (alveoli). a flu-like illness, with a cough, fever, a feeling of illness (malaise), fatigue, and weight loss, heralds the onset in about 50% of people. frequent presence of crackling sounds (called velcro crackles) when the doctor listens with a stethoscope.
term.synonym: idiopathic bronchiolitis obliterans with organizing pneumonia

term.name: respiratory bronchiolitis-associated interstitial lung disease
term.def: a idiopathic interstitial pneumonia which involves bronchiolocentric alveolar macrophage accumulation, mild bronchiolar fibrosis and chronic inflammation. respiratory bronchiolitis is a histopathologic lesion found in cigarette smokers and is characterized by the presence of pigmented intralumenal macrophages within first- and second-order respiratory bronchioles.

term.name: lymphoid interstitial pneumonia
term.def: a idiopathic interstitial pneumonia which involves diffuse interstitial infiltration of involved areas mostly with t lymphocytes, plasma cells, and macrophages. lymphoid hyperplasia is frequently seen. onset is often slow with gradually increasing cough and breathlessness over 3 or more years. fever, weight loss, chest pain, and arthralgia are occasionally found. crackles may be detected as the disease progresses.

term.name: inhalation anthrax
term.def: an anthrax disease that results_in infection located_in lung lymph nodes brought on by breathing in the spores of the bacteria bacillus anthracis. the first symptoms of inhalation anthrax are like cold or flu symptoms and can include a sore throat, mild fever and muscle aches. later symptoms include cough, chest discomfort, shortness of breath, tiredness and muscle aches.

term.name: lower respiratory tract disease
term.def: a respiratory system disease which involves the lower respiratory tract.

term.name: tuberculous mesenteric gland
term.def: a tuberculosis and is_a lymph node disease that involves infection of the mesenteric glands by tuberculosis causing mycobacteria. the symptoms include distended abdomen, persistent intestinal indigestion, diarrhea, flatulence, and abdominal pain.

term.name: autoimmune polyendocrine syndrome type 1
term.def: an autoimmune polyendocrine syndrome that is inherited in an autosomal recessive fashion, which is characterized by abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes auto-reactivity against endocrine organs.

term.name: autoimmune polyendocrine syndrome type 2
term.def: an autoimmune polyendocrine syndrome that is characterized by abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes auto-reactivity against endocrine organs. it is more heterogeneous and has not been linked to one gene.

term.name: cutaneous lupus erythematosus
term.def: a lupus erythematosus and is_a skin disease that causes skin lesions on parts of the body that are exposed to sunlight.

term.name: jamestown canyon encephalitis
term.def: a california virus encephalitis that results_in inflammation located_in brain, has_agent jamestown canyon virus, which is transmitted_by culiseta, transmitted_by aedes, and transmitted_by anopheles species of mosquitoes. the infection has_symptom headache, has_symptom fever, has_symptom neck stiffness, has_symptom photophobia, has_symptom nausea, has_symptom vomiting, and has_symptom seizures.

term.name: snowshoe hare encephalitis
term.def: a california virus encephalitis that results_in inflammation located_in brain, has_agent snowshoe hare virus, which is transmitted_by aedes mosquitoes. the infection has_symptom headache, has_symptom fever, has_symptom anorexia, and has_symptom seizures.

term.name: trivittatus encephalitis
term.def: a california virus encephalitis that results_in inflammation located_in brain, has_agent trivittatus virus, which is transmitted_by ochlerotatus trivittatus mosquito. the infection has_symptom headache, has_symptom fever, has_symptom disorientation, has_symptom tremors, has_symptom convulsions, has_symptom paralysis, and has_symptom coma.

term.name: inkoo encephalitis
term.def: a california virus encephalitis that results_in inflammation located_in brain, has_agent inkoo virus, which is transmitted_by ochlerotatus communis mosquito. the infection has_symptom stiff neck, has_symptom lethargy, has_symptom headache, has_symptom fever, and has_symptom seizures.

term.name: kunjin encephalitis
term.def: a west nile encephalitis that results_in infection located_in brain, has_agent kunjin virus, a subtype of west nile virus, which is transmitted_by culex annulirostris mosquito bite. the infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom rigor, has_symptom headache, has_symptom confusion, and has_symptom lethargy.

term.name: tick-borne encephalitis
term.def: a flavivirus infectious disease and is_a viral encephalitis that results_in inflammation located_in brain, has_agent tick-borne encephalitis virus, which is transmitted_by ixodes ticks. the infection has_symptom drowsiness, has_symptom confusion, has_symptom sensory disturbances, and has_symptom paralysis.

term.name: siberian tick-borne encephalitis
term.def: a tick-borne encephalitis that results_in inflammation located_in brain, has_agent siberian subtype of tick-borne encephalitis virus, which is transmitted_by ixodes persulcatus ticks. the infection has_symptom drowsiness, has_symptom confusion, has_symptom sensory disturbances, and has_symptom paralysis.

term.name: simple genetic disease
term.def: a genetic disease that is the result of one or more abnormal alleles and may be dominant (a single copy of the abnormal allele is sufficient to give rise to the disease), semi-dominant, or recessive (requiring both copies of the gene to have an abnormal allele).

term.name: complex genetic disease
term.def: a genetic disease that require multiple abnormal alleles to manifest are complex. these diseases are termed multifactorial or polygenic. expressivity or penetrance of the disease is complex and is associated with multiple genes in combination with lifestyle and environmental factors. multifactoral genetic diseases include heart disease and diabetes, although a subset of diabetes may be classified as a simple genetic disease (due to the presence of a single abnormal allele).

term.name: powassan encephalitis
term.def: a flavivirus infectious disease and is_a viral encephalitis that results_in inflammation located_in brain, has_agent powassan virus, which is transmitted_by ixodes and transmitted_by dermacentor species of ticks. the infection has_symptom headache, has_symptom fever, has_symptom vomiting, has_symptom stiff neck, has_symptom sleepiness, has_symptom breathing distress, has_symptom tremors, has_symptom confusion, has_symptom seizures, has_symptom paralysis, and has_symptom coma.

term.name: colorado tick fever encephalitis
term.def: a reoviridae infectious disease and is_a viral encephalitis that results_in inflammation located_in brain, has_agent colorado tick fever virus which is transmitted_by rocky mountain wood tick, dermacentor andersoni. the infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom headache, has_symptom nausea, has_symptom stiff neck, has_symptom chills, has_symptom hallucinations, has_symptom disorientation, and has_symptom memory loss.

term.name: herpes simplex virus encephalitis
term.def: a simplexvirus infectious disease and is_a viral encephalitis that results_in infection located_in brain, has_agent human herpesvirus 1 or has_agent human herpesvirus 2. the infection has_symptom headache, has_symptom fever, has_symptom personality and behavioral changes, has_symptom seizures, has_symptom partial paralysis, and has_symptom hallucinations.

term.name: varicella-zoster virus encephalitis
term.def: a varicellovirus infectious disease and is_a viral encephalitis that results_in infection located_in brain, has_agent human herpesvirus 3 and has_symptom lethargy, has_symptom rash, has_symptom confusion, has_symptom hallucinations, has_symptom weakness, has_symptom paralysis, has_symptom numbness, and has_symptom parasthesias.

term.name: epstein-barr virus encephalitis
term.def: an epstein-barr virus infectious disease and is_a viral encephalitis that results_in inflammation, located_in brain, has_agent human herpesvirus 4 and has_symptom seizures, has_symptom altered consciousness, and has_symptom cerebellar ataxia.

term.name: measles virus encephalitis
term.def: a measles virus infectious disease and is_a viral encephalitis that results_in inflammation located_in brain, has_agent measles virus, which is transmitted_by contact with oronasal secretions, or semen of an infected person. the infection has_symptom headache, has_symptom irritability, has_symptom drowsiness, has_symptom abnormal reflexes, has_symptom involuntary movements, has_symptom hemiplagia, has_symptom ataxia, has_symptom nystagmus, and has_symptom dysphasia.

term.name: erythema multiforme
term.def: a skin disease that is a type of allergic reaction located_in skin, which occurs in response to medications, infections, or illness.

term.name: cytomegalovirus encephalitis
term.def: a cytomegalovirus infectious disease and is_a viral encephalitis that results_in inflammation, located_in brain, has_agent human herpesvirus 5, has_symptom confusional syndrome, has_symptom seizures, has_symptom coma, has_symptom dysphasia, and has_symptom cranial nerve palsies.

term.name: rubella virus encephalitis
term.def: a rubivirus infectious disease and is_a viral encephalitis that results_in inflammation located_in brain, has_agent rubella virus, which is transmitted_by droplet spread of oronasal secretions from the infected person through coughing and sneezing, and transmitted_by congenital method. the infection has_symptom confusion, has_symptom drowsiness, has_symptom delirium, has_symptom convulsions, has_symptom cranial nerve palsies, and has_symptom coma.

term.name: coxsackievirus encephalitis
term.def: a coxsackievirus infectious disease and is_a viral encephalitis that involves inflammation located_in brain, has_agent group a coxsackievirus or has_agent group b coxsackievirus, which are transmitted_by ingestion of food contaminated with feces, transmitted_by contact with pharyngeal secretions, or transmitted_by droplet spread of oronasal secretions. the infection has_symptom reduced level of consciousness, has_symptom confusion, has_symptom irritability, has_symptom seizures, and has_symptom coma.

term.name: polioencephalitis
term.def: an enterovirus infectious disease and is_a viral encephalitis that results_in inflammation located_in brain, has_agent polioviruses, which are transmitted_by ingestion of food contaminated with feces. the infection has_symptom tremors, has_symptom nystagmus, has_symptom loss of conjugate eye movements, has_symptom muscle rigidity, has_symptom hemiparesis, and has_symptom coma.

term.name: adenovirus encephalitis
term.def: an adenoviridae infectious disease and is_a viral encephalitis that results_in inflammation located_in brain, has_agent human adenoviruses. the symptoms include fever, stupor, nuchal rigidity, loss of consciousness and seizures.

term.name: influenza virus encephalitis
term.def: an orthomyxoviridae infectious disease and is_a viral encephalitis that results_in inflammation located_in brain, has_agent influenza a virus or has_agent influenza b virus, which are transmitted_by droplet spread of oronasal secretions during coughing, sneezing, or talking from an infected person. the infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom reduced consciousness, and has_symptom ocular muscle palsies.

term.name: nipah virus encephalitis
term.def: a henipavirus infectious disease and is_a viral encephalitis that results_in inflammation located_in brain, has_agent nipah virus, which is transmitted_by direct contact with sick person or animals, or their contaminated tissues. the infection has_symptom dizziness, has_symptom drowsiness, has_symptom altered consciousness, has_symptom disorientation, and has_symptom coma.

term.name: lymphocytic choriomeningitis virus encephalitis
term.def: a lymphocytic choriomeningitis and is_a viral encephalitis that results_in inflammation located_in brain, has_agent lymphocytic choriomeningitis virus, which is transmitted_by common house mouse, mus musculus. the infection has_symptom drowsiness, has_symptom confusion, has_symptom sensory disturbances, and has_symptom paralysis.

term.name: argentine hemorrhagic fever
term.def: an arenaviral hemorrhagic fever that results_in infection, has_agent junin virus, which is transmitted_by rodent, calomys musculinus. the infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom fatigue, has_symptom malaise, has_symptom leukopenia, has_symptom thrombocytopenia, and has_symptom hemorrhagic manifestations.

term.name: bolivian hemorrhagic fever
term.def: an arenaviral hemorrhagic fever results_in infection, has_agent machupo virus, which is transmitted_by vesper mouse, calomys callosus. the infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom headache, has_symptom fatigue, has_symptom myalgia, has_symptom arthralgia, has_symptom bleeding from the oral and nasal mucosa, and has_symptom bleeding from the bronchopulmonary, gastrointestinal and genitourinary tracts.

term.name: venezuelan hemorrhagic fever
term.def: an arenaviral hemorrhagic fever that results_in infection, has_agent guanarito virus, which is transmitted_by cotton rat, sigmodon alstoni and transmitted_by cane mouse, zygodontomys brevicauda. the infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom headache, has_symptom myalgia, has_symptom sore throat, has_symptom weakness, has_symptom anorexia, has_symptom nausea, has_symptom vomiting, has_symptom convulsions, has_symptom epistaxis, has_symptom bleeding gums, has_symptom hematemesis, has_symptom melena, and has_symptom menorrhagia.

term.name: brazilian hemorrhagic fever
term.def: an arenaviral hemorrhagic fever that results_in infection, has_agent sabia virus, which is transmitted_by rodents. the infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom eye redness, has_symptom fatigue, has_symptom dizziness, has_symptom muscle aches, has_symptom loss of strength, and has_symptom bleeding under the skin, internal organs, or from body orifices like the mouth, eyes or ears.

term.name: chapare hemorrhagic fever
term.def: an arenaviral hemorrhagic fever that results_in infection, has_agent chapare virus. the infection has_symptom headache, has_symptom joint pain, has_symptom muscle pain, has_symptom vomiting, has_symptom shock, and has_symptom bleeding.

term.name: whitewater arroyo hemorrhagic fever
term.def: an arenaviral hemorrhagic fever that results_in infection, has_agent whitewater arroyo virus, which is transmitted_by white-throated woodrats (neotoma albigula). the infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom headache, has_symptom myalgia, and has_symptom hemorrhagic manifestations.

term.name: korean hemorrhagic fever
term.def: a hemorrhagic fever with renal syndrome that results_in infection located_in kidney, has_agent hantaan virus, which is transmitted_by the eurasian field mouse, apodemus agrarius, or has_agent seoul virus, which is transmitted_by norwegian rat, rattus norvegicus. the infection has_symptom headache, has_symptom back pain, has_symptom abdominal pain, has_symptom fever, has_symptom chills, has_symptom nausea, has_symptom blurred vision, has_symptom flushing of the face, has_symptom redness of the eyes, has_symptom rash, has_symptom low blood pressure, has_symptom acute shock, has_symptom vascular leakage, and has_symptom acute kidney failure, which can cause severe fluid overload.

term.name: nephropathia epidemica
term.def: a hemorrhagic fever with renal syndrome that results_in infection located_in kidney, has_agent puumala virus, which is transmitted_by bank vole, clethrionomys glareolus. the infection has_symptom headache, has_symptom nausea, has_symptom back pain, has_symptom vomiting, has_symptom myalgia, has_symptom abdominal pain, has_symptom internal hemorrhage, and has_symptom renal failure.

term.name: lujo hemorrhagic fever
term.def: an arenaviral hemorrhagic fever that results_in infection, has_agent lujo virus, which has_symptom bleeding.

term.name: cytomegalovirus hepatitis
term.def: a cytomegalovirus infectious disease and is_a viral hepatitis that results_in inflammation, located_in liver, has_agent human herpesvirus 5, has_symptom nausea, has_symptom vomiting, has_symptom headache, has_symptom abdominal pain, has_symptom dark urine, and has_symptom jaundice. clinical feature includes atypical lymphocytes in the blood.

term.name: epstein-barr virus hepatitis
term.def: a viral hepatitis and is_a epstein-barr virus infectious disease that results_in inflammation, located_in liver, has_agent human herpesvirus 4 and has_symptom headache, has_symptom fatigue, has_symptom fever, has_symptom abdominal pain, has_symptom nausea, and has_symptom jaundice.

term.name: herpes simplex virus hepatitis
term.def: a simplexvirus infectious disease and is_a viral hepatitis that results_in inflammation located_in liver, has-agent human herpesvirus 1 or has_agent human herpesvirus 2, and has_symptom fever, has_symptom nausea, has_symptom vomiting, has_symptom abdominal pain, and has_symptom herpetic lesions.

term.name: adenovirus hepatitis
term.def: an adenoviridae infectious disease and is_a viral hepatitis that involves inflammation of the liver caused by human adenoviruses. the symptoms include fever, coagulopathy and gastrointestinal bleeding. histopathological examination reveals widespread hepatic necrosis with hemorrhage.

term.name: rubella virus hepatitis
term.def: a rubivirus infectious disease and is_a viral hepatitis that results_in inflammation located_in liver, has_agent rubella virus, which is transmitted_by droplet spread of oronasal secretions from the infected person through coughing and sneezing, and transmitted_by congenital method. the infection results in hepatic necrosis.

term.name: yellow fever hepatitis
term.def: a yellow fever virus infectious disease and is_a viral hepatitis that results_in inflammation located_in liver, has_agent yellow fever virus. the infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom chills, has_symptom headache, has_symptom myalgia, has_symptom weakness, has_symptom nausea, has_symptom vomiting, has_symptom jaundice, and has_symptom hemorrhagic manifestations.

term.name: measles virus hepatitis
term.def: a measles virus infectious disease and is_a viral hepatitis that results_in inflammation located_in liver, has_agent measles virus, which is transmitted_by contact with oronasal secretions, or semen of an infected person. the infection causes hepatic dysfunction and has_symptom jaundice.

term.name: varicella-zoster virus hepatitis
term.def: a varicellovirus infectious disease and is_a viral hepatitis that results_in inflammation located_in liver, has_agent human herpesvirus 3, has_symptom skin rash, has_symptom oral lesions, has_symptom severe abdominal and back pain, has_symptom fever, has_symptom chills, has_symptom malaise, and has_symptom fatigue.

term.name: swine influenza
term.def: an influenza that results_in infection located_in respiratory tract of pigs and humans, has_agent influenza c virus, or has_agent influenza a virus subtypes (h1n1, h1n2, h3n1, h3n2, and h2n3), which are transmitted_by direct contact with infected pigs. the infection in humans has_symptom fever, has_symptom lethargy, has_symptom lack of appetite, has_symptom coughing, has_symptom runny nose, has_symptom sore throat, has_symptom nausea, has_symptom vomiting, and has_symptom diarrhea.

term.name: campylobacter jejuni gastroenteritis
term.def: a primary campylobacter infectious disease and is_a bacterial gastroenteritis that involves inflammation of the stomach and intestines caused by campylobacter jejuni infection, which is characterized by diarrhea (may be bloody), abdominal pain, fever and vomiting.

term.name: vibrio gastroenteritis
term.def: a vibrio infectious disease and is_a bacterial gastroenteritis that involves inflammation of the stomach and intestines caused by noncholera vibrio species like vibrio parahaemolyticus, vibrio fluvialis and vibrio vulnificus. some species produce enterotoxins, which impair intestinal absorption, resulting in watery diarrhea. the symptoms include abdominal cramps, fever, vomiting, nausea and diarrhea.

term.name: lambert-eaton myasthenic syndrome
term.def: a neuromuscular junction disease that results from an abnormality of acetylcholine (ach) release at the neuromuscular junction. it results from an autoimmune attack against voltage-gated calcium channels (vgcc) on the presynaptic motor nerve terminal.

term.name: staphylococcus gastroenteritis
term.def: a staphylococcal infectious disease and is_a bacterial gastroenteritis that is caused by ingestion of food containing enterotoxins, which are produced by staphylococcal species. the symptoms include abdominal cramps, diarrhea, headache and fever.

term.name: bacillus cereus gastroenteritis
term.def: a primary bacillaceae infectious disease and is_a bacterial gastroenteritis that is caused by ingestion of food contaminated with bacillus cereus, which produces enterotoxins in the intestine. the symptoms include vomiting, abdominal cramps, fever and diarrhea.

term.name: sapovirus gastroenteritis
term.def: a caliciviridae infectious disease and is_a viral gastroenteritis that results_in inflammation located_in stomach and located_in intestine, has_agent sapovirus, which is transmitted_by ingestion of contaminated food. the infection has_symptom nausea, has_symptom vomiting, has_symptom abdominal pain, and has_symptom diarrhea.

term.name: polycystic echinococcosis
term.def: an echinococcosis that is caused by the larvae of echinococcus vogeli or echinococcus oligarthrus, which infect the liver.

term.name: hepeviridae infectious disease
term.def: a (+)ssrna virus infectious disease that results_in infection in animals and humans, located_in liver, has_agent hepeviridae viruses.

term.name: coxiella burnetii pneumonia
term.def: a q fever and is_a bacterial pneumonia that is a zoonotic infectious disease caused by coxiella burnetii, a bacterium which affects both humans and animals. the symptoms include fever, headache, cough, pleuritic chest pain, myalgia and arthralgia. infection of humans usually occurs by inhalation of these organisms from air that contains airborne barnyard dust contaminated by dried placental material, birth fluids, or excreta of infected herd animals, ingestion of contaminated milk, tick bites and human to human transmission.

term.name: coxiella burnetii hepatitis
term.def: a q fever and is_a hepatitis that involves inflammation of the liver caused by coxiella burnetti, which results in the formation of granulomas. the symptoms include fever, malaise, hepatomegaly with right upper abdominal pain, and jaundice.

term.name: selective igm deficiency disease
term.def: a selective immunoglobulin deficiency disease thatis a dysgammaglobulinemia resulting from decreased levels of immunoglobulin m (igm) production to roduction of other antibodies.

term.name: candidal gastritis
term.def: a candidiasis and is_a fungal gastritis that involves inflammation of the gastric mucosa caused by candida albicans infection. the symptoms include dyspepsia, gastric ulcers, gastric perforations, nausea and vomiting.

term.name: helicobacter heilmannii gastritis
term.def: a primary helicobacter infectious disease and is_a bacterial gastritis that involves inflammation of the stomach lining caused by candidatus helicobacter heilmannii, which is associated with peptic ulceration.

term.name: histoplasma capsulatum gastritis
term.def: an american histoplasmosis and is_a fungal gastritis that results_in inflammation, located_in stomach lining in immunocompromised patients, has_agent histoplasma capsulatum var capsulatum, transmitted_by airborne spores and results_in_formation_of gastric mass with ulceration, and results_in_formation_of hypertrophic gastric folds.

term.name: morganella morganii intestinal infectious disease
term.def: an opportunistic enterobacteriaceae infectious disease and is_a intestinal infectious disease that involves infection of the intestine caused by morganella morganii.

term.name: vibrio cholerae o139 cholera
term.def: a cholera that involves infection of the intestine caused by vibrio cholerae o139 strain.

term.name: entamoeba histolytica dysentery
term.def: an amebiasis and is_a protozoal dysentery that involves infection of the intestine with entamoeba histolytica trophozoites, which adhere to and kill colonic epithelial cells causing diarrhea with blood and mucus. the symptoms inlcude abdominal pain and fever.

term.name: escherichia coli dysentery
term.def: an enteroinvasive escherichia coli infectious disease and is_a dysentery that involves infection of the intestine caused by enteroinvasive escherichia coli. the symptoms include fever, bloody diarrhea, and dehydration.

term.name: intestinal capillariasis
term.def: a capillariasis that involves infection of the intestine with capillaria causing abdominal pain, weight loss, stomach growling, depressed levels of potassium and albumin in the blood, and diarrhea.

term.name: hepatic capillariasis
term.def: a capillariasis that involves infection of the liver with capillaria, which manifests as an acute or subacute hepatitis with eosinophilia. the symptoms include abdominal pain, fever, chills, hepatitis, ascites, hepatolithiasis, and hepatomegaly.

term.name: pulmonary capillariasis
term.def: a capillariasis that involves infection of the lungs with capillaria, resulting in fever, cough, asthma, and pneumonia.

term.name: balamuthia mandrillaris infectious disease
term.def: an amoebozoa infectious disease that involves infection caused by a free-living ameba balamuthia mandrillaris resulting in encephalitis and skin lesions in humans and animals.
term.synonym: granulomatous amebic encephalitis due to balamuthia mandrillaris

term.name: acanthamoeba infectious disease
term.def: an amoebozoa infectious disease that involves an infection in humans and animals caused by a parasitic protozoan of genus acanthamoeba, which is an opportunistic pathogen occuring in patients with weakened immune system.

term.name: alveolata infectious disease
term.def: a parasitic protozoa infectious disease that involves infection caused by alveolates, which are single-celled eukaryotes.

term.name: heterolobosea infectious disease
term.def: a parasitic protozoa infectious disease that involves infection caused by the members of the class heterolobosea, which move with eruptive bulges and show transformation to a temporary flagellate stage.

term.name: euglenozoa infectious disease
term.def: a parasitic protozoa infectious disease that involves infection caused by euglenozoans, which are single-celled flagellates.

term.name: parabasalia infectious disease
term.def: a parasitic protozoa infectious disease that involves infection caused by parabasalids, which are anaerobic flagellated protozoans.

term.name: fornicata infectious disease
term.def: a parasitic protozoa infectious disease that involves infection caused by fornicates, which are unicellular flagellates with one or two karyomastigonts per cell.

term.name: trichomonadida infectious disease
term.def: a parabasalia infectious disease that involves infection with anaerobic flagellate parasites belonging to the order trichomonadida. they typically have four to six flagella at the cell's apical pole.

term.name: tritrichomonadida infectious disease
term.def: a parabasalia infectious disease that involves infection with anaerobic flagellate parasites belonging to the order tritrichomonadida, which are characterized by a single mastigont with four flagella, and both a comb-like structure and an infrakinetosomal body.

term.name: primary amebic meningoencephalitis
term.def: a heterolobosea infectious disease and is_a meningoencephalitis that involves infection of the central nervous system caused by naegleria fowleri. the symptoms include headache, nausea, rigidity of the neck muscles, vomiting, delirium, seizures and coma.

term.name: apicomplexa infectious disease
term.def: an alveolata infectious disease that involves infection caused by the members of the phylum apicomplexa, which are unicellular, spore forming parasites of animals and humans.

term.name: coccidia infectious disease
term.def: an apicomplexa infectious disease that involves infection caused by the members of the class coccidia, which are spore-forming, single-celled and obligate intracellular parasites of the intestinal tract of animals and humans.

term.name: aconoidasida infectious disease
term.def: an apicomplexa infectious disease that involves infection caused by the members of the class aconoidasida.

term.name: acanthamoeba encephalitis
term.def: an acanthamoeba infectious disease and is_a encephalitis that results in infection of the brain caused by acanthamoeba. the symptoms include headaches, altered mental status, and focal neurologic deficit, which progresses over several weeks to death.
term.synonym: granulomatous amebic encephalitis due to acanthamoeba

term.name: parasitic stramenopiles infectious disease
term.def: a parasitic infectious disease that involves infection caused by parasitic members of the taxon stramenopiles, in which the flagellate cells possess two different shaped flagella. this taxon contains both unicellular and multicellular organisms.

term.name: brugia timori filariasis
term.def: a filarial elephantiasis that involves parasitic infection by the nematode brugia timori, which inhabits the lymphatics. the symptoms include fever and chronic lymphedema.

term.name: philophthalmiasis
term.def: a parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection of the eyes by philophthalmus species. external ocular philophthalmiasis manifests as follicular conjunctivitis and superficial keratitis. sub-conjunctival ocular philophthalmiasis consists of a mild edema with minimal cellular reaction.

term.name: coenurosis
term.def: a parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves infection by metacestode larval stage (coenurus) of taenia multiceps or taenia serialis. coenuri in the skin or subcutaneous tissue present as painless nodules, which manifest on the trunk, sclera, subconjuctiva, neck, shoulders, head and limbs. coenuri in the central nervous system may cause headache, fever, vomiting, nerve palsies, jacksonian epilepsy, pachymeningitis, obstructive or communicating hydrocephalus, and intracranial arteritis with transient hemiparesis. coenuri in the eye cause both intraocular and orbital infections.

term.name: dipylidium caninum infectious disease
term.def: a parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection in dogs, cats and humans caused by cysticercoid larvae of dipylidium caninum through ingestion of larvae contaminated flea, which results in diarrhea and restlessness.

term.name: mesocestoidiasis
term.def: a parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic cestode infection caused by mesocestoides lineatus resulting in nausea, diarrhea, abdominal discomfort and vomiting.

term.name: acanthocephaliasis
term.def: a parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves infection of the intestine caused by thorny-headed worms macracanthorhynchus or moniliformis moniliformis. the symptoms include abdominal pain and distension, fever, decreased appetite, nausea, vomiting, weight loss, diarrhea, and constipation or bloody stools.

term.name: uncinaria stenocephala infectious disease
term.def: a parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease and is_a intestinal infectious disease that involves infection of the small intestine in humans, cats, dogs and foxes by the nematode uncinaria stenocephala. the symptoms include diarrhea and hypoproteinemia in heavier infections.

term.name: angiostrongyliasis
term.def: a parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection of the intestine, central nervous system and eyes by angiostrongylus cantonensis or angiostrongylus costaricensis.

term.name: angiostrongylus cantonensis infectious disease
term.def: an angiostrongyliasis that involves infection of the brain by the larvae of angiostrongylus cantonensis causing eosinophilic meningitis. the symptoms include severe headache, nausea, vomiting, neck stiffness, seizures, and neurologic abnormalities. ocular invasion by the larvae can occur.

term.name: angiostrongylus costaricensis infectious disease
term.def: an angiostrongyliasis that involves infection of the intestine by angiostrongylus costaricensis, which is characterized by the formation of granulomas with heavy eosinophilic infiltration in the abdominal cavity.

term.name: baylisascariasis
term.def: a parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection of the intestine caused by the larvae of baylisascaris procyonis, which can invade the spinal cord, brain, and eye of humans, resulting in permanent neurologic damage, blindness, or death.

term.name: dioctophymiasis
term.def: a parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection by the nematode dioctophyme renale in humans after eating undercooked food. the larvae are found in the subcutaneous nodules and kidneys.

term.name: thelaziasis
term.def: a parasitic helminthiasis infectious diseasea and is_a eye disease that involves infection of the eyes in humans by nematode thelazia callipaeda causing varying degrees of inflammation and lacrimation. in heavier infections, photophobia, edema, conjunctivitis, and blindness occurs.

term.name: acoelomata infectious disease
term.def: a parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves infection caused by parasitic worms, which are bilaterian, unsegmented, soft-bodied invertebrate animals with no body cavity.

term.name: pseudocoelomata infectious disease
term.def: a parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves infection caused by parasitic invertebrates, which have a pseudocoel. tissue derived from mesoderm only partly lines the fluid filled body cavity of these animals.

term.name: acanthocephala infectious disease
term.def: a pseudocoelomata infectious disease that involves infection by parasitic worms known as thorny-headed worms, characterized by the presence of an evertable proboscis, armed with spines, which is used to pierce and hold the gut wall of the host.

term.name: tungiasis
term.def: a parasitic ectoparasitic infectious disease that is an inflammatory skin disease caused by the parasitic infestation of the female chigoe flea, tunga penetrans in animals and humans. the symptoms include skin inflammation, severe pain, itching, and a lesion at the site of infection that is characterized by a black dot at the center of a swollen red lesion, surrounded a white halo.

term.name: ancylostoma caninum ancylostomiasis
term.def: an ancylostomiasis that involves infection of the intestine in dogs and humans by the nematode ancylostoma caninum. in humans, the larvae migrate to the intestine causing eosinophilic enteritis. they have also been implicated as a cause of diffuse unilateral subacute neuroretinitis.

term.name: ophthalmomyiasis
term.def: a myiasis that involves parasitic infestation of oestrus ovis larvae in the eye causing severe irritation, edema, and pain.

term.name: trichomonas vaginalis trichomoniasis
term.def: a trichomoniasis that is caused by a singled-celled protozoan parasite trichomonas vaginalis, which is transmitted through sexual contact. symptoms include inflammation of the cervix, urethra and vagina which produce an itching or burning sensation, and yellow-green, itchy, frothy foul-smelling vaginal discharge.

term.name: trichomonas tenax trichomoniasis
term.def: a trichomoniasis that is caused by a singled-celled protozoan parasite trichomonas tenax, which is transmitted through oral droplets, by kissing, or on fomites such as eating utensils. trichomonas tenax causes periodonitis and bronchopulmonary trichomoniasis by aspiration from the oropharynx.

term.name: cutaneous ascomycota mycosis
term.def: a cutaneous mycosis that results_in fungal infection located_in skin, located_in hair and located_in nail, has_agent ascomycota phylum members.

term.name: cutaneous basidiomycota mycosis
term.def: a cutaneous mycosis that results_in fungal infection located_in skin, located_in hair and located_in nail, has_agent basidiomycota phylum members.

term.name: neoscytalidium dimidiatum infectious disease
term.def: an onychomycosis that results_in fungal infection located_in nail, has_agent neoscytalidium dimidiatum and has_symptom rough nail, and has_symptom crumbly nail which can separate from the nail bed.

term.name: scopulariopsis infectious disease
term.def: an opportunistic ascomycota mycosis that has_agent scopulariopsis, which results_in a systemic infection in immunocompromised individuals.

term.name: onychomycosis
term.def: a dermatomycosis that results_in fungal infection located_in nail, has_agent ascomycota fungi which are not dermatophytes and has_symptom opaque nail, has_symptom yellow-brown nail, has_symptom crumbly nail that can separate from the nail bed.

term.name: subcutaneous ascomycota mycosis
term.def: a subcutaneous mycosis that results_in fungal infection located_in skin and located_in subcutaneous tissue, has_agent ascomycota phylum members.

term.name: subcutaneous fungi incertae sedis mycosis
term.def: a subcutaneous mycosis that results_in fungal infection located_in skin and located_in subcutaneous tissue, has_agent fungi incertae sedis taxon members.

term.name: basidiobolomycosis
term.def: an entomophthoromycosis that involves a chronic inflammatory or granulomatous fungal infection of the subcutaneous tissue of the limbs, chest, back or buttocks caused by basidiobolus ranarum. lesions appear as subcutaneous nodules which develop into massive, firm, indurated, painless swellings which are freely movable over the underlying muscle, but are attached to the skin which may become hyperpigmented but not ulcerated.

term.name: conidiobolomycosis
term.def: an entomophthoromycosis that is a chronic inflammatory or granulomatous fungal infection caused by conidiobolus species, which is restricted to the nasal submucosa and characterized by polyps or palpable restricted subcutaneous masses. symptoms include nasal obstruction, drainage and sinus pain. subcutaneous nodules develop in the nasal and perinasal regions.

term.name: superficial ascomycota mycosis
term.def: a superficial mycosis that results_in fungal infection of the outermost layer located_in skin and located_in hair shaft, has_agent ascomycota phylum members.

term.name: superficial basidiomycota mycosis
term.def: a superficial mycosis that results_in fungal infection of the outermost layer located_in skin and located_in hair shaft, has_agent basidiomycota phylum members.

term.name: primary systemic ascomycota mycosis
term.def: a primary systemic mycosis that results_in fungal infection located_in human body, has_agent ascomycota phylum members.

term.name: stachybotrys infectious disease
term.def: a primary systemic ascomycota mycosis that results_in systemic fungal infection in animals and humans, has_agent stachybotrys chartarum, transmitted_by airborne spores and transmitted_by vehicle-borne ingestion and the fungus produces trichothecene mycotoxins including satratoxins causing pulmonary hemorrhage in infants.

term.name: opportunistic ascomycota mycosis
term.def: an opportunistic mycosis that involves infection of the body by fungi belonging to the phylum ascomycota.

term.name: opportunistic basidiomycota mycosis
term.def: an opportunistic mycosis that results_in fungal infection located_in human body, has_agent basidiomycota phylum members.

term.name: opportunistic fungi incertae sedis mycosis
term.def: an opportunistic mycosis that results_in fungal infection located_in human body, has_agent fungi incertae sedis taxon members.

term.name: opportunistic microsporidia mycosis
term.def: an opportunistic mycosis that results_in fungal infection located_in human body, has_agent microsporidia phylum members.

term.name: penicilliosis
term.def: an opportunistic ascomycota mycosis that has_agent penicillium marneffei, results_in systemic infection and has_symptom fever, has_symptom anemia, has_symptom weight loss, has_symptom lymphadenopathy, has_symptom hepatosplenomegaly, has_symptom respiratory signs, and has_symptom skin lesions.

term.name: fusariosis
term.def: an opportunistic ascomycota mycosis that involves localized or hematogenously disseminated fungal infection by fusarium species. skin lesions are seen in neutropenic patients, and indolent cellulitis or soft-tissue necrosis occur in immunocompromised patients at the site of trauma.

term.name: trichosporonosis
term.def: an opportunistic basidiomycota mycosis that results_in disseminated infection, has_agent trichosporon and results_in_formation_of nontender erythematous nodules anywhere on the body.

term.name: parasitic ichthyosporea infectious disease
term.def: a parasitic infectious disease that involves parasitic infection by the members of the class ichthyosporea, which are parasites of fish and other animals.

term.name: primary systemic mycosis
term.def: a systemic mycosis that results_in infection located_in human body, has_agent fungi, which can overcome the physiological and cellular defences of the normal human host. the primary deep pathogens usually gain access to the host via the respiratory tract.

term.name: scopulariopsis brevicaulis infectious disease
term.def: a scopulariopsis infectious disease and is_a onychomycosis that results_in fungal infection located_in nail, has_agent scopulariopsis brevicaulis and has_symptom rough nail, and has_symptom crumbly nail which can separate from the nail bed.

term.name: scytalidium hyalinum infectious disease
term.def: a dermatomycosis that results_in fungal infection located_in hand, foot and nail of toe by scytalidium hyalinum, resulting_in_formation_of lesions and has_symptom keratotic plantar surface.

term.name: cutaneous sporotrichosis
term.def: a sporotrichosis and is_a subcutaneous ascomycota mycosis that results_in fungal infection located_in skin and located_in subcutaneous tissue through direct inoculation from wood splinters or hay, has_agent sporothrix schenckii, a dimorphic fungus, which results_in_formation_of erythematous papulonodular lesions evolving into either smooth or verrucose painless nodules that may ulcerate and drain.

term.name: asfarviridae infectious disease
term.def: a dsdna virus infectious disease that results_in infection in pigs, has_agent asfarviridae viruses, which are transmitted_by soft tick bite.

term.name: adenoviridae infectious disease
term.def: a dsdna virus infectious disease that results_in infection in cattle, dogs, horses, pigs, and humans, has_agent adenoviridae viruses.

term.name: simplexvirus infectious disease
term.def: a herpesviridae infectious disease that results_in infection in animals and humans, has_agent simplexvirus.

term.name: deltavirus infectious disease
term.def: a (-)ssrna virus infectious disease that results_in infection located_in liver in humans, has_agent deltavirus.

term.name: polyomaviridae infectious disease
term.def: a dsdna virus infectious disease that results_in infection in animals and humans, has_agent polyomaviridae viruses.

term.name: varicellovirus infectious disease
term.def: a herpesviridae infectious disease that results_in infection in animals and humans, has_agent varicellovirus.

term.name: hepacivirus infectious disease
term.def: a flaviviridae infectious disease that results_in infection, has_agent hepacivirus, which is transmitted_by sexual contact, or transmitted_by blood transfusion.

term.name: arteriviridae infectious disease
term.def: a nidovirales infectious disease that results_in infection in animals, has_agent arteriviridae viruses.

term.name: bornaviridae infectious disease
term.def: a mononegavirales infectious disease that results_in infection in animals and humans, has_agent bornaviridae viruses.

term.name: alkhurma hemorrhagic fever
term.def: a flavivirus infectious disease that results_in infection, has_agent alkhurma hemorrhagic fever virus, which is transmitted_by ornithodoros savignyi tick bite, transmitted_by ingestion of unpasteurized camel milk, or transmitted_by entry via skin wound. the infection has_symptom headache, has_symptom joint pain, has_symptom muscle pain, has_symptom vomiting, has_symptom thrombocytopenia, and has_symptom hemorrhagic fever.

term.name: measles virus infectious disease
term.def: a morbillivirus infectious disease that results_in infection, has_agent measles virus, which is transmitted_by droplet spread, or trasnmitted_by contact of oronasal secretions from an infected person.

term.name: physical disorder
term.def: a disorder that has an available objective mechanical test (such as chemical tests or brain scans), and are diagnosed only by behavioral syndrome (such as those in the diagnostic and statistical manual of mental disorders (dsm).

term.name: genetic disorder
term.def: a medical disorder that is an illness caused by abnormalities in genes or chromosomes.

term.name: congenital hypothyroidism
term.synonym: congenital hypothyroidism not due to iodine deficiency

term.name: mental disorder
term.def: a disorder that is a psychological or behavioral pattern associated with distress or disability that occurs in an individual and is not a part of normal development or culture.

term.name: ladd syndrome
term.def: a simple genetic disease that is characterized by abnormalities affecting the lacrimal and salivary glands and ducts, ears, teeth and fingers and toes.

term.name: primary bacterial infectious disease
term.def: a bacterial infectious disease that results_in infection by bacteria as a result of their presence or activity within the normal, healthy host, and their intrinsic virulence is, in part, a necessary consequence of their need to reproduce and spread.

term.name: commensal bacterial infectious disease
term.def: a bacterial infectious disease that results_in infection by bacteria which are part of the normal human flora when one or more of the defense mechanisms designed to restrict them from the usually sterile internal tissues are breached by accident, by intent (surgery), or by an underlying metabolic or an infectious disorder.

term.name: opportunistic bacterial infectious disease
term.def: a bacterial infectious disease that results_in infection by bacteria in individuals whose host defense mechanisms have been compromised.

term.name: commensal actinomycetales infectious disease
term.def: a commensal bacterial infectious disease that results_in infection, has_agent actinomycetales bacteria, which are part of the normal human flora.

term.name: foodborne botulism
term.def: a botulism that involves intoxication caused by botulinum neurotoxins (bonta, b, e and f), which are transmitted_by ingestion of food contaminated with preformed toxins, has_agent clostridium botulinum a, has_agent clostridium botulinum b, has_agent clostridium botulinum e and has_agent clostridium botulinum f. the infection has_symptom blurred vision, has_symptom diplopia, has_symptom dysarthria, has_symptom dysphonia, has_symptom dysphagia and has_symptom descending muscle paralysis.

term.name: wound botulism
term.def: a botulism that involves intoxication caused by botulinum neurotoxins (bonta, b, e and f), has_agent clostridium botulinum a, has_agent clostridium botulinum b, has_agent clostridium botulinum e and has_agent clostridium botulinum f, which are transmitted_by contact of spores with the open wounds, which then reproduce in an anaerobic environment to produce toxins.

term.name: infant botulism
term.def: a botulism that involves intoxication caused by botulinum neurotoxins (bonta or b) in infants, has_agent clostridium botulinum a or has_agent clostridium botulinum b, which are transmitted_by ingestion of bacterial spores, which then grow in the intestine and release toxins. the infection has_symptom constipation, has_symptom lethargy, has_symptom difficulty feeding, has_symptom swallowing, has_symptom ptosis, has_symptom loss of head control, and has_symptom muscle weakness.

term.name: familial adenomatous polyposis
term.def: a simple genetic disease that is caused by mutations in teh apc gene and involves formation of numerous polyps in the epithelium of the large intestine which are initially benign and later transform into colon cancer.

term.name: x-linked asperger syndrome
term.def: an autism spectrum disorder that is characterized by significant difficulties in social interaction, along with restricted and repetitive patterns of behavior and interests. it differs from other autism spectrum disorders by its relative preservation of linguistic and cognitive development.

term.name: hereditary hypophosphatemic rickets
term.def: a rickets that results_from a x-linked dominant mutation in the phex gene which results_in excess phosphate secretion that impairs bone mineralization.

term.name: campomelic dysplasia
term.def: an osteochondrodysplasia that results_from a mutation in chromosome 17 which results_in bowing in the located_in tibia and located_in femur.

term.name: papillomaviridae infectious disease
term.def: a dsdna virus infectious disease that results_in infection in animals and humans, has_agent papillomaviridae viruses.

term.name: exanthema subitum
term.def: a roseolovirus infectious disease and is_a viral exanthem that results_in infection in infants and children, located_in skin, has_agent human herpesvirus 6 or has_agent human herpesvirus 7 and has_symptom sudden high fever, and has_symptom red rash that occurs first on the trunk then spreading to legs and neck.

term.name: banna virus encephalitis
term.def: a reoviridae infectious disease and is_a viral encephalitis that results_in inflammation located_in brain, has_agent banna virus, which is transmitted_by culex, and transmitted_by anopheles mosquitoes. the infection has_symptom fever, and has_symptom headache.

term.name: anelloviridae infectious disease
term.def: a ssdna virus infectious disease that results_in infection in humans, has_agent anelloviridae viruses.

term.name: dsdna virus infectious disease
term.def: a dna virus infectious disease that results_in infection, has_agent dsdna viruses, which possess double-stranded dna.
term.synonym: double stranded dna virus infectious disease

term.name: ssdna virus infectious disease
term.def: a dna virus infectious disease that results_in infection, has_agent ssdna viruses, which possess single-stranded dna.
term.synonym: single stranded dna virus infectious disease

term.name: dsdna-rt virus infectious disease
term.def: a dna virus infectious disease that results_in infection, has_agent dsdna retro-transcribing viruses, which possess double-stranded dna genomes and replicate using reverse transcriptase.
term.synonym: double stranded dna reverse transcribing virus infectious disease
double stranded dna-reverse transcribing virus infection

term.name: dsrna virus infectious disease
term.def: a rna virus infectious disease that results_in infection, has_agent dsrna viruses, which possess double-stranded rna genomes.
term.synonym: double stranded rna virus infectious disease

term.name: (+)ssrna virus infectious disease
term.def: a rna virus infectious disease that results_in infection, has_agent ssrna positive-strand viruses, no dna stage, which possess positive-sense single-stranded rna genomes.
term.synonym: positive stranded ssrna virus infectious disease
positive-sense single stranded rna virus infectious disease

term.name: (-)ssrna virus infectious disease
term.def: a rna virus infectious disease that results_in infection, has_agent ssrna negative-strand viruses, which have negative-sense single-stranded rna genomes.
term.synonym: negative stranded ssrna virus infectious disease
negative-sense single stranded rna virus infectious disease

term.name: ssrna-rt virus infectious disease
term.def: a rna virus infectious disease that results_in infection, has_agent ssrna retro-transcribing viruses, which possess single-stranded rna genomes and replicate using reverse transcriptase.
term.synonym: single stranded rna reverse transcribing virus infectious disease

term.name: human papilloma virus related anal squamous cell carcinoma
term.def: a human papillomavirus related squamous cell carcinoma and is_a anal squamous cell carcinoma that results_in infection located_in anus, has_agent human papillomavirus (types 16 or 18), which cause malignant tumors in squamous epithelium of anus.
term.is_a: human papillomavirus related squamous cell carcinoma

term.name: human papilloma virus related vaginal squamous cell carcinoma
term.def: a human papillomavirus related squamous cell carcinoma and is_a squamous cell carcinoma that results_in infection located_in vagina, has_agent human papillomavirus (type16), which cause malignant tumors in squamous epithelium of the vagina.
term.is_a: human papillomavirus related squamous cell carcinoma

term.name: variola major
term.def: a smallpox that results_in severe infection, located_in skin, has_agent variola virus. the infection results_in_formation_of lesions.

term.name: human torovirus gastroenteritis
term.def: a torovirus infectious disease and is_a viral gastroenteritis that results_in inflammation located_in stomach and located_in intestine, has_agent human torovirus, which is transmitted_by ingestion of food contaminated with feces. the infection has_symptom bloody diarrhea.

term.name: saffold virus gastroenteritis
term.def: a cardiovirus infectious disease and is_a viral gastroenteritis that results_in inflammation located_in stomach and located_in intestine, has_agent saffold virus, which is transmitted_by ingestion of food contaminated with feces. the infection has_symptom watery diarrhea, has_symptom fever, has_symptom nausea, and has_symptom vomiting.

term.name: spinal polio
term.def: a paralytic poliomyelitis that results_in destruction located_in motor neurons of spinal cord, has_agent human poliovirus 1, has_agent human poliovirus 2, or has_agent human poliovirus 3, which are transmitted_by ingestion of food or water contaminated with feces, or transmitted_by direct contact with the oral secretions. the infection has_symptom difficulty breathing, and has_symptom paralysis of arms and legs.

term.name: bulbospinal polio
term.def: a paralytic poliomyelitis that results_in destruction located_in motor neurons of brainstem and located_in motor neurons of spinal cord, has_agent human poliovirus 1, has_agent human poliovirus 2, or has_agent human poliovirus 3, which are transmitted_by ingestion of food or water contaminated with feces, or transmitted_by direct contact with the oral secretions. the infection has_symptom difficulty breathing, has_symptom difficulty swallowing, and has_symptom paralysis of arms and legs.

term.name: paralytic poliomyelitis
term.def: a poliomyelitis and is_a motor neuron disease that results_in destruction located_in motor neurons of central nervous system, has_agent human poliovirus 1, has_agent human poliovirus 2, or has_agent human poliovirus 3, which are transmitted_by ingestion of food or water contaminated with feces, or transmitted_by direct contact with the oral secretions. the infection has_symptom loss of reflexes, has_symptom muscle spasms, and has_symptom acute flaccid paralysis.

term.name: o'nyong'nyong fever
term.def: an alphavirus infectious disease and is_a arthritis that results_in infection located_in joint, has_agent o'nyong-nyong virus, which is transmitted_by anopheles gambiae, and transmitted_by anopheles funestus mosquitoes. the infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom arthralgia, has_symptom rash, and has_symptom lymphadenitis.

term.name: barmah forest virus disease
