term.def: an alphavirus infectious disease and is_a arthritis that results_in infection located_in joint, has_agent barmah forest virus, which is transmitted_by mosquito bite. the infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom arthralgia, and has_symptom rash.

term.name: ross river virus disease
term.def: an alphavirus infectious disease and is_a polyarthritis that results_in infection located_in joint, has_agent ross river virus, which is transmitted_by culex, and transmitted_by aedes mosquitoes. the infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom arthralgia, and has_symptom rash.

term.name: lymphocytic choriomeningitis virus meningitis
term.def: a lymphocytic choriomeningitis and is_a viral meningitis that results_in inflammation located_in meninges, has_agent lymphocytic choriomeningitis virus, which is transmitted_by common house mouse, mus musculus. the infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom headache, and has_symptom stiff neck.

term.name: lymphocytic choriomeningitis virus meningoencephalitis
term.def: a lymphocytic choriomeningitis and is_a meningoencephalitis that results_in inflammation located_in meninges and located_in brain, has_agent lymphocytic choriomeningitis virus, which is transmitted_by common house mouse, mus musculus. the infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom headache, has_symptom stiff neck, has_symptom drowsiness, has_symptom confusion, has_symptom sensory disturbances, and has_symptom paralysis.

term.name: oropouche fever
term.def: a bunyaviridae infectious disease that results_in infection, has_agent oropouche virus, which is transmitted_by biting midge, culicoides paraensis. the infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom chills, has_symptom headache, has_symptom anorexia, has_symptom muscle pain, has_symptom joint pain, and has_symptom vomiting.

term.name: balkan hemorrhagic fever
term.def: a hemorrhagic fever with renal syndrome that results_in infection located_in kidney, has_agent dobrava-belgrade virus , which is transmitted_by yellow-necked field mouse, apodemus flavicollis. the infection has_symptom headache, has_symptom fever, has_symptom muscle pains, has_symptom facial flush, has_symptom petechiae, has_symptom hemorrhagic features, has_symptom proteinuria, and has_symptom renal failure.

term.name: adult t-cell leukemia
term.def: a human t-lymphotropic virus 1 infectious disease and is_a t-cell leukemia that results_in abnormal increase of lymphocytes, derives_from t-cells, has_agent human t-lymphotropic virus 1, which is transmitted_by sexual contact, transmitted_by contaminated needles used by intravenous-drug users, and transmitted_by breast feeding. the infection results_in_formation_of skin lesions.

term.name: gamstorp-wohlfart syndrome
term.synonym: myokymia, myotonia, muscle wasting, and hyperhidrosis

term.name: intermediate spinal muscular atrophy
term.synonym: muscular atrophy, spinal, infantile chronic form

term.name: hypermethioninemia
term.is_a: inborn errors of amino acid metabolism

term.name: congenital adrenal insufficiency
term.synonym: adrenal insufficiency, congenital, with 46,xy sex reversal, partial or complete

term.name: saldino-noonan syndrome
term.synonym: type i short rib polydactyly syndrome

term.name: jmp syndrome
term.def: a simple genetic disease that is an autosomal recessive autoinflammatory disorder characterized by childhood onset of joint stiffness and severe contractures of the hands and feet, erythematous skin lesions with subsequent development of severe lipodystrophy.
term.synonym: joint contractures, muscular atrophy, microcytic anemia, and panniculitis-induced lipodystrophy

term.name: congenital muscular dystrophy
term.def: a muscular dystrophy that is an autosomal recessive disorder present at birth, which may result in contractures, scoliosis, respiratory and swallowing difficulties, and foot deformities.

term.name: nonsyndromic deafness
term.def: an auditory system disease that is associated with permanent hearing loss caused by damage to structures in the inner ear and/or the middle ear, which is not associated with other signs and symptoms.

term.name: spondylocostal dysostosis
term.def: a dysostosis that results_in abnormal development located_in vertebrae and located_in ribs. the bones of the spine do not develop properly, which causes them to be misshapen and abnormally joined together.

term.name: congenital disorder of glycosylation type i
congenital disorder of glycosylation type ii
cone-rod dystrophy
term.def: a retinal degeneration that is an inherited progressive disease that causes deterioration of the cone and rod photoreceptor cells and often results in blindness.

term.name: 2-hydroxyglutaric aciduria
term.def: an inborn errors of metabolism that is an autosomal recessive neurometabolic disorder characterized by the significant elevation of urinary levels of hydroxyglutaric acid.

term.name: senior-loken syndrome
term.def: a simple genetic disease that is inherited as an autosomal recessive genetic trait. this disorder is characterized by progressive wasting of the filtering unit of the kidney (nephronophthisis), with or without medullary cystic renal disease, and progressive eye disease.

term.name: occult macular dystrophy
term.def: a macular degeneration that is characterized by a central cone dysfunction leading to a loss of vision with a normal fundus and normal fluorescein angiography findings.

term.name: infective endocarditis
term.def: a heart disease involving inflammation of the endocardium (inner layer of the heart) caused by bacterial infection.

term.name: c1 inhibitor deficiency
term.def: a complement deficiency that is a functional deficiency in the complement component c1 inhibitor leading to hereditary angioedema (hae) involving swelling due to leakage of fluid from blood vessels into connective tissue.

term.name: autoimmune disease of central nervous system
term.def: an autoimmune disease of the central nervous system.
term.is_a: autoimmune disease of the nervous system

term.name: autoimmune disease of endocrine system
term.def: an autoimmune disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system resulting in production of antibodies or t cells against cells and/or tissues in the endocrine system.

term.name: artemis deficiency
term.def: a severe combined immunodeficiency that is caused when the dclrei1, dna cross-link repair 1c gene contains mutations resulting in the inability to repair dna.

term.name: cd3zeta deficiency
term.def: a severe combined immunodeficiency that affects the development and function of t cells.

term.name: omenn syndrome
term.def: a combined t cell and b cell immunodeficiency that is an autosomal recessive immunodeficiency associated with mutations in the recombination activating genes (rag1 and rag2), affecting circulating levels of both b-cells and t-cells.
term.is_a: combined t cell and b cell immunodeficiency

term.name: recombinase activating gene 1 deficiency
term.def: a severe combined immunodeficiency that is the result of a mutation on chromosome 6 rag1 gene involving genetic rearrangement of both the t- and b-lymphocyte receptor genes.

term.name: recombinase activating gene 2 deficiency
term.def: a severe combined immunodeficiency that is the result of a mutation on chromosome 6 rag2 gene involving genetic rearrangement of both the t- and b-lymphocyte receptor genes.

term.name: gamma chain deficiency
term.def: a severe combined immunodeficiency that is a x-linked scid caused by mutations in genes encoding common gamma chain proteins shared by the interleukin (il-2,4,7,9,16 and21) receptors resulting in a non-functional gamma chain, defective interleukin signalling, minimal or ascent t- and nk cells and non-functional b-cells.

term.name: cd45 deficiency
term.def: a severe combined immunodeficiency that is an autosomal recessive disease with t and b lymphocyte dysfunction, due to a large deletion at one allelle and a point mutation at the other. the point mutation resulted in the alteration of intervening sequence 13 donor splice site. the population of t lymphocytes is diminished and unresponsive to mitogen stimulation. the level of b lymphocyte numbers, serum immunoglobulin decreased with age.

term.name: interleukin-7 receptor alpha deficiency
term.def: a severe combined immunodeficiency that results from defective il7r expression causes t-b+nk+ scid. loss of il-7r function leads to the loss of an antiapoptotic signal, resulting in a loss of t-cell selection in thymus.

term.name: cd3delta deficiency
term.def: a severe combined immunodeficiency that is characterized by the absence of t cells but normal numbers of b cells. cd3d is essential for t cell development.

term.name: cd3epsilon deficiency
term.def: a severe combined immunodeficiency that is an autosomal recessive immunodeficiency caused by mutations in the gene coding for t-cell surface glycoprotein cd3epsilon chain precursors. patients with cd3epsilon deficiency have a severe defect in the expression of the t-cell receptor cd3-complex.

term.name: cd3gamma deficiency
term.def: a severe combined immunodeficiency an autosomal recessive immunodeficiency caused by mutations in the gene coding for t-cell surface glycoprotein cd3gamma chain precursors. patients with cd3gamma deficiency have a severe defect in the expression of the t-cell receptor cd3-complex. affected patients have decreased t-cell numbers and function; b cells are variably affected.

term.name: coronin-1a deficiency
term.def: a severe combined immunodeficiency that is an actin regulator when mutated results in scid through inhibition of thymic egress of mature thymocytes into peripheral lymphoid organs.

term.name: reticular dysgenesis
term.def: a severe combined immunodeficiency that is the most severe form of scid and is caused by mutations in the gene encoding mitochondrial adenylate kinase 2. it is characterized by congenital agranulocytosis, lymphopenia, and lymphoid and thymic hypoplasia with absent cellular and humoral immunity functions.

term.name: dna ligase iv deficiency
term.def: a combined t cell and b cell immunodeficiency that is caused by a mutatino in the lig4 gene, a dna ligase, encoding a protein essential for v(d)j recombination and dna double-strand break (dsb) repair through nonhomologous end joining (nhej). patients present with immunodeficiency and developmental and growth delay.
term.is_a: combined t cell and b cell immunodeficiency

term.name: cd40 ligand deficiency
term.def: a combined t cell and b cell immunodeficiency that is a x-linked immunodeficiency with hyperimmunoglobulin m (xhim) affecting isotype switching and is caused by the absence of cd40 ligand which is normally expressed on activated cd4+ t cells. individuals with this mutation are unable to switch from igm to igg, iga and ige.
term.is_a: combined t cell and b cell immunodeficiency

term.name: cd40 deficiency
term.def: a combined t cell and b cell immunodeficiency that is caused by mutation in tnfrsf5 resulting in type 3 hyper-igm immunodeficiency characterized by an inability of b cells to undergo isotype switching, an inability to mount an antibody-specific immune response, and a lack of germinal center formation.
term.is_a: combined t cell and b cell immunodeficiency

term.name: lambda 5 deficiency
term.def: a b cell deficiency that is caused by mutations in the igll1 gene. lambda 5 mutations an cause a block in b cell development at the transition between the pro-b cell and the pre-b cell stage.

term.name: immunoglobulin alpha deficiency
term.def: a b cell deficiency that is an autosomal recessive disorder caused by mutation in the iga (cd79 alpha) antigen receptor.

term.name: b cell linker protein deficiency
term.def: a hypobammaglobulinemia that is a b cell deficiency caused by a mutation a cytoplasmic linker or adaptor protein that plays a critical role in b cell development, the b cell linker protein (blnk) gene. mutations in this gene cause hypoglobulinemia and absent b cells, a disease in which the pro- to pre-b-cell transition is developmentally blocked. the blnk gene is associated with intracellular calcium mobilization, essential for cell activation.

term.name: good syndrome
term.def: an agammaglobulinemia that is a condition where there is co-occurrence of deficient cell-mediated immunity and benign thymoma.

term.name: autoimmune disease of exocrine system
term.def: an immune system disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or t cells against cells and/or tissues in the exocrine system.

term.name: autoimmune disease of eyes, ear, nose and throat
term.def: an autoimmune disease of the eyes, ears, nose and throat.

term.name: autoimmune disease of gastrointestinal tract
term.def: an autoimmune disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or t cells against cells and/or tissues in the gastrointestinal tract.

term.name: autoimmune disease of musculoskeletal system
term.def: an autoimmune disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or t cells against cells and/or tissues in the musculoskeletal system.

term.name: autoimmune disease of peripheral nervous system
term.def: an autoimmune disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or t cells against cells and/or tissues in the peripheral nervous system.
term.is_a: autoimmune disease of the nervous system

term.name: medical disorder
term.def: a disease that is present at birth due to a genetic abnormality, error with embryonic development, infection or compromised intrauterine environment.

term.name: developmental disease of mental health
term.def: a disease of mental health that occur during a child's developmental period between birth and age 18 resulting in retarding of the child's psycholotgical or physical development.

term.name: specific developmental disease
term.def: a developmental disease of mental health that categorizes specific learning disabilities and developmental disorders affecting coordination.

term.name: autoimmune disease of skin and connective tissue
term.def: an autoimmune disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or t cells against cells and/or tissues in the skin and connective tissue.

term.name: pervasive developmental disease
term.def: a developmental disease of mental health that refers to a group of five disorders characterized by delays in the development of multiple basic functions including socialization and communication.

term.name: autism spectrum disease
term.def: a pervasive developmental disease that is a spectrum of psychological conditions characterized by widespread abnormalities of social interactions and communication, as well as severely restricted interests and highly repetitive behavior.

term.name: atypical autism
term.def: an autism spectrum disorder that involves some autistic symptoms occuring after age 3 with an abscence of all the traits necessary for a diagnosis of autism.

term.name: aphasia
term.def: a language disease that involves an acquired impairment of any laguage modality such as producting or comprehending spoken or written language.

term.name: writing disease
term.def: a learning disability that involves impaired written language ability such as impairments in handwriting, spelling, organization of ideas, and composition.

term.name: nosophobia
term.def: a specific phobia that involves an irrational fear of contracting a disease.

term.name: autoimmune disease of urogenital tract
term.def: an autoimmune disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or t cells against cells and/or tissues in the urogenital tract.

term.name: autoimmune disease of blood
term.def: an autoimmune disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or t cells against cells and/or tissues in the blood.

term.name: autoimmune disease of cardiovascular system
term.def: an autoimmune disease that is the abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes your immune system to produce antibodies or t cells against cells and/or tissues in the cardiovascular system.

term.name: neurological disorder
term.def: a physical disorder that is the result of structural, biochemical or electrical abnormalities in the brain or spinal cord, or in the nerves leading to or from them, can result in symptoms such as paralysis, muscle weakness, poor coordination, loss of sensation, seizures, confusion, pain and altered levels of consciousness.

term.name: peripheral neuropathy
term.def: a neuropathy that is located_in nerves of the peripheral nervous system.

term.name: lymphoma
term.def: a cancer that affects lymphocytes that reside in the lymphatic system and in blood-forming organs.
term.synonym: malignant lymphoma nos of unspecified site (disorder)
malignant lymphoma, no icd-o subtype (morphologic abnormality)

term.name: cutaneous t cell lymphoma
term.def: a non-hodgkin's lymphoma that is caused by a mutation of t cells.

term.name: familial juvenile hyperuricemic nephropathy
term.def: a kidney disease that is characterized by hyperuricemia with renal uric acid under-excretion, gout and chronic kidney disease.

term.name: pearson syndrome
term.def: a mitochondrial disease that is characterized by sideroblastic anemia and exocrine pancreas dysfunction.

term.name: neoplastic disease
term.def: a disease of cellular proliferation that results in an abnormal mass of tissue.

term.name: blastoma
term.def: a cancer that results_from malignant growth located_in immature blood forming cells called blast cells. blast cells are also referred to as bone marrow precursor cells or simply precursor cells.

term.name: myeloma
term.def: a bone marrow cancer that affects plasma cells in which abnormal plasma cells multiply uncontrollably in the bone marrow and occasionally in other parts of the body.

term.name: bone disease
term.def: a musculoskeletal system disease that affects the structure or development of bone or causes an impairment of normal bone function.

term.name: bone remodeling disease
term.def: a bone disease that results_in formation or resorption abnormalities located_in bone.

term.name: bone development disease
term.def: a bone disease that results_in abnormal growth and development located_in bone or located_in cartilage.

term.name: bone deterioration disease
term.def: a bone structure disease that results_in change or damage of structure located_in bone.

term.name: ischemic bone disease
term.def: a bone disease that results_in an interruption of blood supply located_in bone.

term.name: bone structure disease

term.def: a parasitic ectoparasitic infectious disease that involves parasitic infestation by members of the subclass hirudinea. the leeches remain attached to their hosts and feed on blood until they become full, at which point they fall off to digest. while feeding, they release an anesthetic and use a combination of mucus and suction to stay attached and secrete an anti-clotting enzyme, hirudin, into the host's blood stream.

term.name: myiasis
term.def: a parasitic ectoparasitic infectious disease that is caused by parasitic dipterous fly larvae (maggots) feeding on the host's necrotic or living tissue.

term.name: asphyxia neonatorum
term.synonym: unspecified severity of birth asphyxia in liveborn infant

term.name: perinatal respiratory disorder
term.synonym: respiratory condition of fetus or newborn (disorder)
unspecified respiratory condition of fetus and newborn

term.name: salmonella gastroenteritis
term.def: a salmonella infectious disease and is_a bacterial gastroenteritis that involves inflammation of the stomach and intestines caused by salmonella infection. the symptoms include diarrhea, vomiting, abdominal pain, fever and weakness.

term.name: bacterial gastroenteritis
term.def: a gastroenteritis that involves inflammation of the stomach and intestines caused by bacteria. the symptoms include abdominal cramps and pain, diarrhea, loss of appetite, nausea, and vomiting.

term.name: pulmonary syphilis
term.def: a tertiary syphilis and is_a lung disease that is caused by the spirochetal bacterium treponema pallidum subspecies pallidum. it is a sexually transmitted disease although congenital syphilis can also occur. treponema infection of the lung leads to a fibrous induration spreading from the roots of the lungs. ulcerations occur in the superficial tissues, while in the deep tissues gummata are formed. symptoms include dry cough, hemoptysis, hemorrhage, dyspnea, pain in the chest, loss of weight and slight fever.

term.name: q fever
term.def: a primary coxiellaceae infectious disease that is a zoonotic infectious disease caused by coxiella burnetii, a bacterium that affects both humans and animals. the symptoms include fever, headache, cough, pleuritic chest pain, myalgia and arthralgia. infection of humans usually occurs by inhalation of these organisms from air that contains airborne barnyard dust contaminated by dried placental material, birth fluids, or excreta of infected herd animals, ingestion of contaminated milk, tick bites and human to human transmission.

term.name: glaucoma associated with anterior segment anomaly
term.synonym: glaucoma associated with anterior segment anomaly (disorder)
glaucoma associated with other anterior segment anomalies

term.name: malignant neoplasm of cervical part of esophagus
term.synonym: malignant neoplasm of the cervical esophagus
malignant tumor of cervical part of esophagus (disorder)
term.is_a: malignant neoplasm of upper third of esophagus
malignant esophageal neoplasm by anatomic region

term.name: psychosexual dysfunction with female orgasmic disease
gilles de la tourette syndrome
term.def: a tic disease that is characterized by multiple physical (motor) tics and at least one vocal (phonic) tic present for more than a year.

term.name: malignant esophageal neoplasm by anatomic region
esophagus sarcoma
term.def: a sarcoma and malignant neoplasm of esophagus that is_located in the esophagus.

term.name: vascular lesions of cord complicating labor and delivery
term.synonym: antepartum vascular lesions of cord complicating labor and delivery
vascular lesions of cord complicating labor and delivery, delivered

term.name: sarcoma
term.def: a cancer that affects connective tissue resulting in mesoderm proliferation.
term.synonym: tumor of soft tissue and skeleton

term.name: glaucoma due to raised episcleral venous pressure
term.synonym: glaucoma with increased episcleral venous pressure
glaucoma with increased episcleral venous pressure (disorder)

term.name: disorder of optic chiasm associated with non-pituitary neoplasm
term.synonym: disorder of optic chiasm associated with non-pituitary neoplasm (disorder)
disorder of optic chiasm associated with other neoplasm

term.name: pertussis
term.def: a commensal alcaligenaceae infectious disease and is_a respiratory system disease that is caused by bacteria of the genus bordetella characterized by a prolonged, high-pitched, deeply indrawn breath (whoop). the bacterium bordetella pertussis causes a highly contagious form of whooping cough, and a milder disease is caused by bordetella parapertussis.

term.name: common wart
term.def: a papillomavirus infectious disease and is_a skin disease that results_in infection located_in skin, has_agent human papillomavirus (types 2 and 4). this infection has_symptom raised wart with roughened surface, most common on hands, but can grow anywhere on the body.

term.name: papillomavirus infectious disease
term.def: a papillomaviridae infectious disease that has_agent human papillomaviruses, which establish productive infections only in the stratified epithelium of the skin or mucous membranes. these viruses cause warts and sometimes tumors. they are transmitted_by sexual contact.

term.name: uterine cervix condylomata acuminata
term.def: an anogenital venereal wart and is_a cervix disease that results_in infection located_in cervix, has_agent human papillomaviruses (types 6 and 11), which are transmitted_by direct sexual contact with the skin of an infected partner. the infection has_symptom cervical warts.

term.name: anogenital venereal wart
term.def: a papillomavirus infectious disease and is_a skin disease that results_in infection located_in skin of vagina, cervix, uterus, anus, penis, scrotum, mouth, and throat, has_agent human papillomaviruses (types 6 and 11), which are transmitted_by direct contact with the skin during oral, genital, or anal sex with an infected partner. the infection has_symptom anogenital warts.
term.synonym: anogenital human papilloma virus infectious disease

term.name: vaginal condylomata acuminata
term.def: an anogenital venereal wart and is_a vaginal disease that results_in infection located_in mucosa of vagina, has_agent human papillomaviruses (types 6 and 11), which are transmitted_by direct sexual contact with the skin of an infected partner. the infection has_symptom vaginal warts.

term.name: vulvar condylomata acuminata
term.def: an anogenital venereal wart and is_a vulvar disease that results_in infection located_in skin of vulva, has_agent human papillomaviruses (types 6 and 11), which are transmitted_by direct sexual contact with the skin of an infected partner. the infection has_symptom vulvar warts.

term.name: urethral condylomata acuminata
term.def: an anogenital venereal wart and is_a urethral disease that results_in infection located_in skin of urethra, has_agent human papillomaviruses (types 6 and 11), which are transmitted_by direct sexual contact with the skin of an infected partner. the infection has_symptom urethral warts.

term.name: anal condylomata acuminata
term.def: an anogenital venereal wart and is_a anus disease that results_in infection located_in skin of anus, has_agent human papillomaviruses (types 6 and 11), which are transmitted_by direct contact with the skin during anal sex with an infected partner. the infection has_symptom anal warts.

term.name: otitis media with effusion
term.def: a non-suppurative otitis media which is a collection of fluid that occurs in the middle ear space as a result of the negative pressure produced by altered eustachian tube function. this can occur from viral upper respiratory infection or bacterial infection, or it can precede and/or follow acute bacterial otitis media.

term.name: non-suppurative otitis media
term.def: a otitis media which involves transudation of fluid in the middle ear without pus formation.
term.synonym: nonsuppurative otitis media, not specified as acute or chronic

term.name: serous glue ear
term.def: a otitis media with effusion with very thick and glue-like middle ear fluid which may cause conductive hearing impairment.

term.name: chronic otitis media with effusion
term.def: a non-suppurative otitis media and eustachian tube disorder which is persistent and long-lasting.

term.name: allescheriosis
term.def: a primary systemic ascomycota mycosis that results_in systemic fungal infection, has_agent pseudallescheria boydii, which results_in_formation_of abscesses.

term.name: large for dates affecting management of mother
term.synonym: antepartum excessive fetal growth affecting management of mother
excessive fetal growth affecting management of mother, delivered
excessive fetal growth, affecting management of mother, antepartum
excessive fetal growth, affecting management of mother, delivered

term.name: pseudomembranous conjunctivitis
term.def: a acute conjunctivitis which involves a fibrin-rich exudate formation on the surface of the conjunctiva. infectious causes of pseudomembranes include corynebacterium diphtheriae, streptococci, pneumococci, herpes simplex virus, adenovirus, chlamydia and gonococci. other causes include chemical (alkali) irritants, erythema multiforme, and ocular pemphigoid.

term.name: syndactyly
term.def: a synostosis that results_in the fusion of two or more digits.

term.name: acute laryngopharyngitis
term.def: an upper respiratory tract disease which involves inflammation of both larynx and pharynx.

term.name: digeorge syndrome
term.def: a t cell deficiency disease that is the result of a large deletion of chromosome 22 which includes the dgs gene needed for development of the thymus and related glands with subsequent lack of t-cell production.

term.name: esophageal varix
term.synonym: esophageal varices in disease classified elsewhere, with bleeding

esophageal varices without mention of bleeding

term.name: allergic conjunctivitis
term.def: a chronic conjunctivitis that is an inflammation of the conjunctiva involing red, itchy, and watery eyes a resulting from an exposure to an allergen or an irritant.

term.name: premature rupture of the fetal membranes
chronic tympanitis
term.synonym: chronic myringitis without mention of otitis media

term.name: diverticulitis of small intestine
term.synonym: diverticulosis of small intestine with hemorrhage

term.name: acute hemorrhagic conjunctivitis
term.def: an enterovirus infectious disease and is_a acute conjunctivitis that results_in inflammation located in conjunctiva, has_agent human coxsackievirus a24 or has_agent human enterovirus 70, which are transmitted_by contaminated fomites or transmitted_by contact with contaminated hands. the infection has_symptom vascular dilation, has_symptom eyelid edema, has_symptom photophobia, has_symptom redness of the eyes, has_symptom watering of the eye, has_symptom conjunctival congestion, and has_symptom superficial punctate epithelial keratitis.

term.name: hemorrhagic disease of newborn
term.synonym: hemorrhagic disease of the newborn due to vitamin k deficiency (disorder)

term.name: typhus
term.synonym: epidemic louse-borne typhus fever due to rickettsia prowazekii

term.name: social phobia
term.def: a phobic disease that involves social anxiety occurring only in specific public or social situations, interactions with others or being evaluated or scrutinized by other people.

term.name: cytomegalovirus infectious disease
term.def: a herpesviridae infectious disease that results_in infection in animals and humans, has_agent cytomegalovirus, which is transmitted_by contact with the infected person's bodily fluids or transmitted_by sexual contact, or transmitted_by blood transfusions.

term.name: rabies
term.def: a rhabdoviridae infectious disease and is_a encephalomyelitis that results_in inflammation located_in brain and located_in spinal cord, has_agent rabies virus, which is transmitted_by bite of an infected animal, or transmitted_by contact of mucous membranes with saliva of an infected animal. the infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom headache, has_symptom prickling or itching sensation at the site of bite, has_symptom anxiety, has_symptom confusion, has_symptom agitation, has_symptom delirium, has_symptom difficulty swallowing, has_symptom hydrophobia, and has_symptom paralysis.

term.name: foot and mouth disease
term.def: a picornaviridae infectious disease that results_in infection in cattle and swine, has_agent foot-and-mouth disease virus, which is transmitted_by contaminated fomites, or transmitted_by ingestion of food contaminated with infected meat or animal products. the infection results_in_formation_of vesicles in the mouth, or on the feet and has_symptom lameness.

term.name: chlamydia trachomatis infectious disease
term.def: a commensal chlamydiaceae infectious disease that is caused by a member of the genus chlamydia, specifically c. trachomatis.

term.name: trachoma
term.def: a chlamydial trachomatis infectious disease and eye disease that is located_in eye.

term.name: hemorrhagic fever with renal syndrome
term.def: a hantavirus infectious disease and is_a renal infectious disease that results_in infection located_in kidney, has_agent hantaan virus, has_agent dobrava-belgrade virus, has_agent seoul virus, or has_agent puumala virus, which are carried and transmitted_by rodents. the infection has_symptom headache, has_symptom fever, has_symptom muscle pains, has_symptom facial flush, has_symptom petechiae, has_symptom hemorrhagic features, has_symptom proteinuria, and has_symptom renal failure.

term.name: hypertension secondary to renal disease, complicating pregnancy, childbirth and the puerperium
term.synonym: hypertension secondary to renal disease, antepartum
hypertension secondary to renal disease, postpartum
hypertension secondary to renal disease, with delivery

term.name: tick paralysis
term.def: a tick infestation and is_a neuromuscular disease that is characterized by an acute, ascending, flaccid motor paralysis, which is caused by the introduction of a neurotoxin into humans during attachment and feeding by the females of several tick species such as dermacentor andersoni, dermacentor variabilis, amblyomma americanum, amblyomma maculatum, ixodes scapularis, ixodes pacificus, ixodes holocyclus, rhipicephalus sanguineus and otobius megnini. the symptoms include local inflammation, edema and hemorrhage.

term.name: conditions involving the integument and temperature regulation of fetus and newborn
ventilation pneumonitis
term.def: an extrinsic allergic alveolitis caused by inhalation of antigens from thermophilic actinomycetes species growing in air conditioners and humidifiers. fungi like aureobasidium sp and candida albicans that survive in the contaminated water in humidifiers and air conditioners are also known to cause the disease.

term.name: vertebral artery occlusion
term.synonym: occlusion and stenosis of vertebral artery

term.name: cercarial dermatitis
term.def: a schistosomiasis and is_a skin disease that is a short-term, cutaneous inflammatory response associated with penetration of the skin by cercariae of bird schistosome, austrobilharzia variglandis. symptoms include reddening and itching of exposed skin in the water or immediately after emerging. itchy, raised papules occur within hours of infection.

term.name: subchronic state latent schizophrenia with acute exacerbation
histoplasma duboisii retinitis
term.def: an african histoplasmosis and is_a histoplasmosis retinitis that results_in inflammation located_in retina, has_agent histoplasma capsulatum var duboisii, transmitted_by airborne spores and results_in_formation_of lesions.

term.name: african histoplasmosis
term.def: a histoplasmosis that results_in systemic fungal infection, has_agent histoplasma capsulatum var duboisii, transmitted_by airborne spores and results_in_formation_of nodules, results_in_formation_of ulcers and results_in_formation_of osteolytic bone lesions.

term.name: kyasanur forest disease
term.def: a flavivirus infectious disease that results_in infection, has_agent kyasanur forest disease virus, which is transmitted_by haemaphysalis spinigera tick bite. the infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom headache, has_symptom stiffness of the neck, has_symptom severe muscle pain, has_symptom cough, has_symptom dehydration, and has_symptom bleeding problems.

term.name: acute schizophrenic episode subchronic state with acute exacerbation
ainhum
term.def: ainhum is a tropical disease where the cause is unknown that results in increasing fibrous constriction and ultimately in spontaneous amputation of the toes and especially the little toes. a painful constriction of the base of the fifth toe frequently followed by bilateral spontaneous amputation (autoamputation) a few years later. the disease occurs predominantly in black africans and their descendants. the exact etiology is still unclear. the true cause of ainhum remains unclear. it is not due to infection by parasites, fungi, bacteria or virus, and it is not related to injury.

term.name: rhinoscleroma
term.def: a primary klebsiella infectious disease and is_a upper respiratory tract disease that involves the inflammation of mucosa lining the nasal cavity, pharynx, larynx, trachea and bronchi that is characterized by the formation of granulomas, dense induration of the tissues and nodular deformity caused by klebsiella rhinoscleromatis.

term.name: necrobacillosis
term.def: a fusobacterium infectious disease which is characterized by systemic sepsis and multisystem abscesses caused by anaerobes of oropharyngeal origin characterized by inflammation and ulcerative or necrotic lesions from which a bacterium of the genus fusobacterium (f. necrophorum synonym sphaerophorus necrophorus) has been isolated. the disease often first presents as a severe tonsillitis or pharyngitis with high-grade fever and chills together with leukocytosis, cervical pain and neck swelling. metastatic abscesses are common in the lung, with associated pleuritic chest pain and haemoptysis.

term.name: pneumocystis jirovecii pneumonia
term.def: a pneumocystis infectious disease and is_a pneumonia that is located_in lungs, has_agent pneumocystis jirovecii that effects interstitial and alveolar tissues and has_symptom nonproductive cough, has_symptom shortness of breath, and has_symptom fever.

term.name: pneumocystis infectious disease
term.def: an opportunistic ascomycota mycosis that has_agent pneumocystis jirovecii, located_in lymph node, located_in spleen, located_in liver and located_in bone marrow, results_in_formation_of lesions.

term.name: fungal lung infectious disease
term.def: a lung disease that is a mycosis caused by fungal growth in the lungs.

term.name: weil's disease
term.def: a leptospirosis that involves infection caused by a spirochete of the genus leptospira, which results in jaundice, chills, fever, muscle pain, and hepatomegaly. hemorrhages occur due to capillary injury and include epistaxis, petechiae, purpura, and ecchymoses that rarely progress to subarachnoid, adrenal, or gastrointestinal hemorrhages. the disease is characterized by meningitis, liver damage and renal failure.

term.name: epilepsia partialis continua with intractable epilepsy
phlebotomus fever
term.def: a bunyaviridae infectious disease that results_in infection, has_agent sandfly fever naples virus, or has_agent sandfly fever sicilian virus, which are transmitted_by phlebotomus papatasi sandfly. the infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom severe frontal headaches, has_symptom muscle ache, has_symptom joint aches, has_symptom flushing of the face, and has_symptom tachycardia.

term.name: calculus of gallbladder and bile duct with acute cholecystitis
term.synonym: calculus of gallbladder and bile duct with acute cholecystitis, with obstruction

term.name: shigella sonnei infectious disease
term.def: a shigellosis that involves infection of the intestine by shigella sonnei.

term.name: gnathomiasis
term.def: a parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves parasitic infection due to migrating immature worms of gnathostoma spinigerum or gnathostoma hispidum, which occurs by eating undercooked fish or poultry containing third-stage larvae, or by drinking water containing infective second-stage larvae in cyclops. migration in the subcutaneous tissues causes intermittent, migratory, painful, pruritic swellings (cutaneous larva migrans). migration to other tissues (visceral larva migrans), result in cough, hematuria, and ocular involvement, with the most serious manifestations eosinophilic meningitis with myeloencephalitis.

term.name: spinal meningioma
term.is_a: spinal canal and spinal cord meningioma

term.name: expressive language disease
term.def: a language disease that involves difficulties with verbal and written expression characterized by an ability to use expressive spoken language that is markedly below the appropriate level for the mental age, but with a language comprehension that is within normal limits.

term.name: epidural abscess
term.def: epidural abscess is a cns abscess characterized by a collection of pus (infected material) between the outer covering of the brain and spinal cord and the bones of the skull or spine. the abscess causes swelling in the area. epidural abscess is a rare disorder caused by infection in the area between the bones of the skull or spine, and the membranes covering the brain and spinal cord (meninges). this infectious disease is called an intracranial epidural abscess if it is inside the skull area, or a spinal epidural abscess if it is found in the spine area. nine out of 10 cases are located in the spine.

term.name: adult respiratory distress syndrome
term.def: a respiratory failure that results from diffuse injury to the endothelium of the lung (as in sepsis, chest trauma, massive blood transfusion, aspiration of the gastric contents, or pneumonia) and is characterized by pulmonary edema with an abnormally high amount of protein in the edematous fluid and by difficult rapid breathing and hypoxemia.

term.name: spinal canal and spinal cord meningioma
term.synonym: meningioma of the spinal canal and spinal cord

term.name: diphtheritic laryngotracheitis
term.def: a diphtheria and is_a laryngotracheitis that involves a bluish white membrane formation on the larynx. it can be an extension of the nasopharyngeal diphtheria. this membrane can lead to airway obstruction, coma, and death. symptoms include fever, hoarseness, and a barking cough.

term.name: diphtheria
term.def: a primary corynebacteriaceae infectious disease and is_a upper respiratory tract disease that is characterized by sore throat, low fever, and an adherent membrane (a pseudomembrane) on the tonsils, pharynx, and/or nasal cavity. a milder form of diphtheria can be restricted to the skin. it is caused by corynebacterium diphtheriae, an aerobic gram-positive bacterium. diphtheria toxin spreads through the bloodstream and can lead to potentially life-threatening complications that affect other organs of the body, such as the heart and kidneys.

term.name: trichomonas urethritis
term.def: a trichomonas vaginalis trichomoniasis and is_a urethritis that involves inflammation of the urethra caused by trichomonas vaginalis, which results in pain during urination.

term.synonym: perinatal jaundice due to hepatocellular damage (disorder)

term.def: a bone fragility disease that results_from a drop in estrogen or testosterone which results_in the thinning of bone tissue and loss of bone mineral density.

term.synonym: vitamin a deficiency with night blindness (disorder)

term.def: a otitis media which involves inflammation of the middle ear with infected effusion containing pus.

term.name: benign hypertensive renal disease
term.synonym: hypertensive renal disease, benign, without mention of renal failure

term.name: clostridium perfringens gastroenteritis
term.def: a commensal clostridium infectious disease and is_a bacterial gastroenteritis that is caused by ingestion of food contaminated with clostridium perfringens, which produces an enterotoxin that acts on the small intestine. the symptoms include watery diarrhea, abdominal cramps, a severe decrease in blood pressure and abdominal expansion from gas.

term.def: a syndrome that is a neurological disorder affecting the pupil of the eye and the autonomic nervous system. it is characterized by one eye with a pupil that is larger than normal and constricts slowly in bright light (tonic pupil), along with the absence of deep tendon reflexes, usually in the achilles tendon.

term.name: acute serous otitis media
term.def: a acute transudative otitis media with thin, watery and sterile effusion.

term.name: acute allergic serous otitis media
term.def: a acute serous otitis media caused by an allergen.

term.def: an arthritis that results_from the accumulation of salt crystals located_in joint.

term.name: palindromic rheumatism
term.def: a syndrome that results_from sudden and rapidly developing attacks of arthritis with a remission period that results_in no joint damage or symptoms.

term.name: onchocerciasis
term.def: a filariasis that involves parasitic infection caused by the nematode onchocerca volvulus, which is transmitted to humans through the bite of a blackfly of the genus simulium. the worms spread throughout the body and, when they die, cause intense itching and a strong immune system response that can destroy nearby tissue. the symptoms include pruritus, dermatitis, onchocercomata (subcutaneous nodules), and lymphadenopathy.

term.name: ocular onchocerciasis
term.def: a onchocerciasis and is_a corneal disease that involves parasitic infection of the eye by the larvae of onchocerca volvulus. the microfilariae migrate to the surface of the cornea. punctate keratitis occurs in the infected area. in severe infection, sclerosing keratitis occurs, making the affected area become opaque leading to blindness.

term.name: acute apical periodontitis
term.synonym: acute apical periodontitis of pulpal origin
acute apical periodontitis of pulpal origin (disorder)

term.name: intrathoracic lymph node tuberculosis

term.name: selective iga deficiency disease

term.name: dysgammaglobulinemia
term.def: a selective immunoglobulin deficiency disease that is caused by a reduction in some types of gamma globulins.

term.name: diarrhea
term.def: diarrhea is a intestinal disease described as the condition of having frequent loose or liquid bowel movements. acute diarrhea is a common cause of death in developing countries and the second most common cause of infant deaths worldwide. the loss of fluids through diarrhea can cause severe dehydration which is one cause of death in diarrhea sufferers. along with water, sufferers also lose dangerous amounts of important salts, electrolytes, and other nutrients. there are at least four types of diarrhea: secretory diarrhea, osmotic diarrhea, motility-related diarrhea, and inflammatory diarrhea.

term.name: hiv enteropathy
term.def: a human immunodeficiency virus infectious disease and is_a intestinal infectious disease that results_in infection characterized by chronic diarrhea lasting longer than 1 month, without an identified infectious cause after thorough evaluation, in an hiv-positive individual, has_agent human immunodeficiency virus 1 or has_agent human immunodeficiency virus 2. it is observed that hiv-infected individuals have histologic abnormalities of the gastrointestinal mucosa, malabsorption, and lymphocyte depletion causing diarrhea, increased gastrointestinal inflammation, increased intestinal permeability, and malabsorption of bile acid and vitamin b12.

term.name: histoplasma duboisii endocarditis
term.def: an african histoplasmosis and is_a infective endocarditis, results_in inflammation located_in endocardium, has_agent histoplasma capsulatum var duboisii, transmitted_by airborne spores and has_symptom murmurs, has_symptom peripheral edema, has_symptom pulmonary rales, has_symptom petechia and has_symptom skin lesions.

term.name: typhoid fever
term.def: a salmonella infectious disease and is_a intestinal infectious disease that is a communicable systemic illness caused by salmonella enterica subsp enterica serovar typhi, which is marked by fever, diarrhea, prostration, headache, splenomegaly, liver enlargement, eruption of rose-colored spots, leukopenia, and intestinal inflammation.

term.name: porphyria
term.synonym: disorder of porphyrin and hem metabolism

term.name: klebsiella pneumonia
term.def: a commensal klebsiella infectious disease and is_a bacterial pneumonia involving klebsiella pneumoniae infection. patients with klebsiella pneumonia tend to cough up a characteristic sputum that is said to resemble \red-currant jelly\. klebsiella pneumonia tends to affect people with underlying diseases, such as alcoholism, diabetes and chronic lung disease. the symptoms include high fever, rigors and pleuritic pain, and hemoptysis.

term.name: escherichia coli pneumonia
term.def: a commensal escherichia coli infectious disease and is_a bacterial pneumonia that is caused by escherichia coli. the disease results from proliferation of aspirated organisms in terminal airways, usually at multiple sites in the lung. multifocal area of consolidation result and terminal airways and alveoli are filled with proteinaceous fluid, fibrin, neutrophils, and macrophages.

term.name: enzootic pneumonia of calves
term.def: a bovine respiratory disease complex which is an infectious disease in calves involving stress and possibly an initial respiratory viral infection followed by a secondary bacterial infection of the lower respiratory tract. mycoplasmal and bacterial agents including pasteurella multocida, mannheimia haemolytica, and mycoplasma bovis represent the most frequently isolated pathogenic organisms.

term.name: rickettsial pneumonia
term.def: a rickettsiosis and is_a bacterial pneumonia that is caused by the genus rickettsia. this infection results in pleural effusions and pulmonary edema.

term.name: mycoplasma pneumoniae pneumonia
term.def: a mycoplasmal pneumonia that is caused by the bacterial species mycoplasma pneumoniae. the symptoms include chest pain, chills, dry cough which is not bloody, excessive sweating, fever, headache and sore throat.

term.name: mycoplasma hyopneumoniae pneumonia
term.def: a mycoplasmal pneumonia that is a contagious infection of pigs caused my mycoplasma hyopneumoniae resulting in lung lesions and chronic cough.

term.name: salmonella pneumonia
term.def: a salmonella infectious disease and is_a bacterial pneumonia that is caused by gram-negative bacteria of genus salmonella which is rare in adults, although more common in children in the tropics. this infection is complicated by suppuration with lung abscess or empyema formation.

term.name: rift valley fever
term.def: a bunyaviridae infectious disease that results_in infection, has_agent rift valley fever virus, which is transmitted_by aedes mosquitoes. the virus affects domestic animals (cattle, buffalo, sheep, goats, and camels) and humans. the infection has_symptom jaundice, has_symptom vomiting blood, has_symptom passing blood in the feces, has_symptom ecchymoses (caused by bleeding in the skin), has_symptom bleeding from the nose or gums, has_symptom menorrhagia and has_symptom bleeding from venepuncture sites.

term.name: intestinal tuberculosis
term.def: a gastrointestinal tuberculosis and is_a intestinal infectious disease that involves diffuse mucosal fold thickening and formation of ulcers and fistulae by tuberculosis causing mycobacteria. clinical presentations include abdominal pain, gastrointestinal bleeding and obstructive symptoms such as nausea and vomiting.

term.name: enteroinvasive escherichia coli infectious disease
term.def: an escherichia coli intestinal infectious disease that involves infection of the intestine caused by a serological subgroup of escherichia coli called enteroinvasive escherichia coli (eiec), which penetrate and multiply within epithelial cells of the colon causing cell destruction. they do not produce toxins but they possess a specific adhesin, which is an outer membrane protein. the symptoms include dysentery-like diarrhea with fever.
term.synonym: enteroinvasive escherichia coli gastrointestinal tract infection
enteroinvasive escherichia coli gastrointestinal tract infection (disorder)
intestinal infectious disease due to enteroinvasive e. coli

term.name: scheuermann's disease
term.def: an osteochondrosis that results_in abnormal bone growth and curvature located_in thoracic vertebral column.

term.name: anterior nasal diphtheria
term.def: a diphtheria and is_a nose disease that is characterized by a mucopurulent nasal discharge (containing both mucus and pus) which may become blood-tinged. a white membrane usually forms on the nasal septum. the disease is usually fairly mild because of apparent poor systemic absorption of toxin in this location, and it can be terminated rapidly by antitoxin and antibiotic therapy.

term.name: diphtheritic cystitis
term.def: a urinary tract infectious disease which involves inflammation and formation of a dense fibrous false membrane on the mucous membrane of the bladder.

term.name: pseudomembranous diphtheritic conjunctivitis
term.def: a pseudomembranous conjunctivitis characterized by swollen and reddened, hot and painful lids. the corynebacterium diphtheriae bacilli produce profuse exudation which has a tendency to coagulate on the surface of the conjunctiva to form a grayish-white membrane.

term.name: diphtheritic myocarditis
term.def: a myocarditis characterized by dilated cardiomyopathy and a variety of types of dysrhythmia and conduction disturbances. it is caused by corynebacterium diphtheriae.

term.name: nasopharyngeal diphtheria
term.def: a diphtheria and is_a nasopharyngeal disease that involves membrane formation from the faucial tonsil areas over the pharyngeal wall and into the nasopharynx. severe disease may cause marked edema of the submandibular areas and the anterior neck along with lymphadenopathy, giving a characteristic \bullneck\ apprearance.

term.name: diphtheritic peritonitis
term.def: a peritonitis which involves inflammation of peritoneal cavity by corynebacterium diphtheriae.

term.name: paratyphoid a

term.name: african horse sickness

term.name: toxoplasma hepatitis

term.name: congenital toxoplasmosis

term.name: toxoplasma myocarditis
term.def: a toxoplasmosis and is_a myocarditis that involves infection of the heart with toxoplasma gondii resulting in shortness of breath and constricting chest pain.

term.name: reoviridae infectious disease
term.def: a dsrna virus infectious disease that results_in infection in animals and humans, has_agent reoviridae viruses.

term.name: toxoplasma pneumonia
term.def: a toxoplasmosis and is_a pneumonia that is caused by the protozoan toxoplasma gondii which is recognized as pathogen in immunocompromised patients. microscopy of the lung shows fibrinous exudate, and necrotic areas with intra and extracellular tachizoites along the interstitium and alveolar spaces. the symptoms are cough, shortness of breath, high fever and rales.

term.name: ocular toxoplasmosis
term.def: a toxoplasmosis and is_a eye disease that results from reactivation of congenital toxoplasmosis, but rarely with acquired infection. focal necrotizing retinitis and a secondary granulomatous inflammation of the choroid occur. the symptoms include conjunctivitis, ocular pain, blurred vision, and blindness.

term.name: alpha 1-antitrypsin deficiency
term.def: a lung disease that is characterized as a genetic disorder caused by defective production of alpha 1-antitrypsin (a1at), leading to decreased a1at activity in the blood and lungs, and deposition of excessive abnormal a1at protein in liver cells. alpha-1 antitrypsin works to protect the lungs from a naturally occuring destructive enzyme that is produced by the lungs in response to infections and toxins (such as cigarette smoke). without enough a1at, these enzymes slowly destroy the lung tissue causing emphysema. the symptoms include shortness of breath, wheezing, rhonchi, and rales.

term.name: loiasis
term.def: a filariasis and is_a skin and subcutaneous tissue disease that involves parasitic infection of the skin and eyes caused by the nematode loa loa, which is transmitted through the bite of a deer fly or mango fly. the disease is characterized by episodic angioedema in the arms and legs, and cyst-like enlargements of the connective tissue around the sheaths of muscle tendons. dead worms may cause chronic abscesses, which may lead to the formation of granulomatous reactions and fibrosis.

term.name: candidal endocarditis
term.def: a candidiasis and is_a infective endocarditis that results_in inflammation located_in endocardium, has_agent candida, which favors previously damaged or prosthetic heart valves. the source is often an intravascular catheter or contaminated equipment used for illicit intravenous drug injection. the illness has_symptom fever, has_symptom murmur, has_symptom congestive heart failure, has_symptom anemia, and has_symptom splenomegaly.

term.name: candidal otitis externa
